title: baked liver
directions: Place liver in bottom of pan or casserole dish.
Add salt, pepper and chopped apples.
Add the onions, then add water and bacon on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then uncover and brown.

title: brussels sprouts with pecans
directions: Cut a cross in the end of each sprout for more even cooking. Cook in boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain well.
In a deep skillet over low heat, stir sugar and butter until sugar dissolves.
Add sprouts and pecans; toss until well glazed.
Serve hot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch size.
Cover bottom well and sides, 1/2 way up only.
Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and set aside.
In a mixer, cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and continue to beat.
In another small dish, mash the bananas with a fork and stir in the milk.

title: squash patties
directions: Drain squash and onion in colander and sprinkle with salt. Add flour, meal, pepper, cheese and egg; mix well.
Form into patties and fry.

title: yummy no-bake cheesecake
directions: Whip cream cheese with fork until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and mix well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust, cover and chill approximately 45 minutes.
Top with pie filling.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Shut off.
Put almond bark and chips in bowl and put in oven; let melt.
Add peanuts.
Stir.
Drop on wax paper in spoonfuls.

title: french coconut custard
directions: Mix well.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy chicken curry
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
While rice is cooking, chop onion and core and chop apple.
Sprinkle chicken with salt.
In a large skillet, cook chicken in 2 tablespoons of margarine for 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to plate.
Add the remaining margarine to skillet; cook onion for 5 minutes.
Stir in curry powder.
Cook 1 minute.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add apple, raisins and broth; bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes until done (until internal juices run clear or temperature reaches 170°).
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with desired garnish.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook chicken in 4 cups of water for 40 minutes.
Drain and take chicken off the bone.
Add cubes, onion, carrots and simmer 10 minutes.
Add green pepper and next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 10 more minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup water and cornstarch.
Add to chow mein, along with chicken.
Serve over rice or can of noodles.

title: sharp sea shells
directions: Mix cheese and soups together.
Chop onion and green pepper into small chunks.
Saute in butter to soften, then add to soup mixture.
Cook sea shells according to directions (not too soft). Drain well, then add to soup mixture.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit and nut cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add the next 7 ingredients. Bake in layers in greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place raisins, coconut and nuts in food processor, then cook sugar and milk until it forms soft ball stage.
Add egg yolks and beat until thick.
Add fruit and nuts and spread.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand overnight.
Add cherry pie mix.
Cook until rhubarb is mushy.
Remove from heat and add cherry jello.

title: fried summer squash
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices.
Season with salt.
Dredge with cornmeal or flour.
Heat vegetable oil or bacon drippings in heavy skillet.
Add squash, then cover with sugar.
Fry slowly until browned, turning several times.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemonade
directions: Juice lemons and pour juice into a 2-quart pitcher.
Add sugar and water.
Stir until sugar is melted.
Add ice cubes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: recipe of 1985's burleson county kolache(queen's kolaches, ella drgac queen)
directions: Sift flour and set aside.
Combine salt, Crisco, sugar and milk; scald and set aside.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Add eggs to milk mixture after mixture has cooled.
Pour all mixtures together, except 1/2 cup of flour, and beat until smooth. Dough should be sort of sticky.
If dough is not too firm, use all of the 6 cups of flour.
If dough is too firm, do not add the last 1/2 cup of flour.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix together and bake 15 minutes at 350°. Serve warm or cold with chips. (Better warm.)

title: famous barbecue ribs
directions: Boil (cover ribs with water; cook about 1 1/2 hours for really tender ribs). Check in 45 minutes to be sure there is still enough water covering the ribs. Drain THOROUGHLY. Mix the soy sauce and cornstarch. Put boiled ribs in a large Tupperware bowl. Pour mixture over and seal. Refrigerate for a couple of hours. Shake it up, turn it over, etc., several times during the 2 hours to coat all the meat. In the meantime, mix the remaining ingredients.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° to 400° for 30 minutes.
May add raisins and nutmeg, if desired.

title: chicken enchilada ring
directions: Saute 2 cups chicken till cooked through. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Coarsely chop chicken with food chopper, place in large mixing bowl. Add cheese, green chilies, mayonnaise and seasoning mix. Add crushed chips to chicken mixture and mix well. Unroll crescent dough. Separate into triangles. Arrange triangles in a circle on baking stone, pizza pan or large air bake pan with wide ends overlapping in the center and points towards the center. Scoop chicken mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle. Bring points of triangles up over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center off ring. Filling will not be completely covered. Bake 20 to 20 minutes or until brown. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: variety pie
directions: Use alternate layers of cold turkey and cooked wide noodles. Sprinkle each layer with Parmesan cheese and canned cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bake 1 hour or until bubbly at 350°.
Pour a little white wine over if you need moisture.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon until brown and crisp; remove and drain on paper towels.
Dice.
Saute chopped onion and potatoes for a couple of minutes.
Sprinkle with flour; add clam juice and stir to combine. Bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring often, until potatoes are soft, about 15 minutes.
Add half and half and season to taste.
Add minced clams; heat until simmering.
Do not boil.
Add whipping cream.
Sprinkle with parsley and diced bacon.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, a few at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix in mincemeat and apples.
Bake in 2 (16 1/2 x 26-inch) pans in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: Put in blender and whip (covered).
Remove cover to slowly add 3/4 cup salad oil in steady stream (with the blender going).

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage or bacon and set aside. Beat eggs; add cheese and milk.
Mix well.
Add sausage or bacon. Pour in pie crust.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic; add paste and stir, then add sauce. Add 2 paste cans of water and one sauce can of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle oregano and Parmesan cheese into sauce. Let boil on medium-low heat, stirring often.
Sauce is done when thick enough that it doesn't run off spoon.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a prepared pie shell. Place pie on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until knife inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix and roll
on
floured
board
about 1/2-inch thick. Cut out and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sliced tomatoes with basil salad
directions: Slice the tomatoes into round disks; spread them on a large flat plate.
Sprinkle basil on tomatoes, then olive oil.
Yield: 6 servings.
Approximate calories/serving: 50.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Blend 2 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Blend well after each addition.
Add vanilla, nuts and jam.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: spiced tomato and cabbage slaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add salt; toss.
Let mixture stand 1 hour.
Rinse cabbage mixture thoroughly to remove excess salt.
Drain.
Return to bowl.
Combine all remaining ingredients in heavy medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture is hot; do not boil.
Pour dressing over cabbage and mix to coat.
Let slaw stand 1 hour.
(Can be prepared up to 2 days ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)
Drain slaw before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt oleo and add cocoa.
Stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir. With wire whisk, blend in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk. Stir until smooth.
Mix in pecans and
pour into crust. Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until set.
Let cool before serving (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: mama e's pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in hot pan or griddle. Makes about 5 to 6 medium pancakes.

title: pear-apple chutney
directions: Tie peppercorns in a piece of cheesecloth.
Combine peppercorns and remaining ingredients in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring mixture occasionally.
Pour hot mixture into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims. Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process chutney in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 half pints.

title: banana upside-down cake
directions: Melt half oleo (1/4 cup) and brown sugar together in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Slice bananas and arrange in rows on top of brown sugar mixture.
Cream remainder oleo and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy skillet.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove cover and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Make ahead for best flavor!

title: favorite chocolate or lemon dessert(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Mix flour and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, bake at 350° until lightly browned (15 minutes).

title: lite baked rice
directions: Combine and put in buttered casserole with lid.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
In an iron skillet, put grease 1/4-inch deep.
When grease is hot, drop potato mixture by spoonfuls and pat down with spoon.
Brown both sides.
Take out and drain on paper towels.

title: magic broth chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in pot and cover with water. Boil until done. Remove chicken and set aside. Bring liquid to a boil. Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch strips. Tear them up and drop into chicken broth. Cook until thickened by the tortillas. Add seasonings. Separate chicken from the bone and add to the tortilla mixture. Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, vanilla in a bowl.
Mix milk and flour in a pan (make sure most of the lumps are out).
Add sugar mixture. Let simmer to thicken.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: kruschikie(polish)
directions: Mix all ingredients and form a ball. Roll out on floured board about 1/8-inch thick. Cut into strips about 4-inches long. Slit each piece in center and pull dough through the slit. Fry until light brown. Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: heart o' mine cookies
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese together until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to creamed mix; mix well.
Stir in oats; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll on lightly floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch heart cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with thumb to make indentation in center of each cookie; fill with 1/2 teaspoon preserves.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: appetizers - crabbies
directions: Blend softened butter, cheese spread, garlic and seasoned salt. Mix in crab meat. Spread on split English muffins. Freeze or chill 10 minutes. Cut in eighths and broil until bubbly and crisp. These are good even if you are not a fan of crab.

title: sweet and sour lentils with fine noodles
directions: Wash and sort lentils.
Place in a saucepan with 2 cups water. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until tender but firm.
In a small bowl, combine soy sauce, honey, vinegar and ginger.
Mix and set aside.
Cook egg noodles until tender to bite or al dente.
Drain and set aside.
Heat sesame oil over medium heat in a large skillet.
When hot, add garlic and carrot; saute over medium-low heat until carrot is tender-crisp. Add green pepper and green onions; saute just until the onions wilt a bit.
Add cooked lentils and soy sauce and honey mixture. Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Combine all ingredients. Blend well; let stand for a few minutes.
This is even better the next day.

title: mini oreo mystical ice cream pie
directions: Stir cookies into softened ice cream.
Spread in prepared crust.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Garnish as desired. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into wedges to serve.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Break bread crumbs; add broth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat slightly.
Pour into a shallow pan; bake 30 minutes in hot oven.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: aunt louise's lime pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in container (not aluminum); cover with lime and water.
Soak 24 hours.
Drain cucumbers and wash off lime.
Cover with water and soak 3 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a baking dish.
Mix margarine, flour and sugar together and place on top of peaches in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk, butter and egg yolks. Add lemon rind and juice.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in a baking dish; set pan in hot water.
Bake on low rack of oven for 1 hour at 325°.
Cake should be light brown on top.

title: liver and rice
directions: Cover liver in boiling water.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and cut into small cubes.
Brown liver, onion, pepper and celery in hot fat.
Mix rice and tomato juice with liver and vegetables. Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: diet soup
directions: Cook until done, then add 16 ounce can of crushed tomatoes.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and pepper in a large bowl.
Add salt and celery seed.
Heat vinegar and sugar until dissolves.
Cool. Pour over veggies.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir several times.

title: steak cosmopolitan
directions: Saute steak in oil until brown.
Add onion and cook 2 minutes. Stir in carrots, broth and mushrooms with liquid and seasonings. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery and cook 10 minutes more.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Stir into meat/vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice. Serves 6.

title: fajitas
directions: Marinate meat in Italian dressing for 4 hours or longer.
Heat skillet until very hot and add meat, stirring constantly.
Push to sides and add onions.
When onions are transparent, add bell peppers and continue stirring until limp.
Place 1/4 cup of mixture in the middle of tortilla.
Add toppings, roll and enjoy.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Beat egg; add to mixture.
Add rhubarb and milk.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; add to other mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bobotie(south african meat dish)
directions: Fry onions in butter.
Add curry powder.
Add meat and all other ingredients.
Stir until meat is turning brown (half cooked).
Pour into oven dish.
Blend eggs in 1 1/2 cups of milk. Pour over meat.
Put bay leaves on top.
Bake at 350° until milk is set and meat is done.

title: scallops in white wine
directions: Wash scallops and pat dry.
Heat oil in skillet and brown scallops at high heat for 1 minute.
Add wine, tomatoes, basil and pepper.
Lower heat and continue cooking until scallops are cooked through, but not tough and tomatoes are heated.
Serve at once.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix all ingredients together and paint.

title: good apple butter
directions: Quarter and core apples; cook with peelings until done.
Run through sieve.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook all for 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 1/2 pints.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix and spread over top of warm cake.
Place about 3 inches from broiler until mixture browns slightly.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine 1 c. sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Toss with rhubarb. Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into pastry crust.
Combine milk, eggs and 1/2 c. sugar.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with lattice crust. flute edges.
Bake in hot oven 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: ready whenever bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran and let stand 15 minutes.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and cream until fluffy.
Stir in bran.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk.
Fill well-greased tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Mixture will keep 2 or 3 weeks in covered container in refrigerator.
Do not stir.

title: honey holiday mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In large shallow roasting pan, combine popcorn and chow mein noodles.
Melt margarine and stir in seasonings.
Pour over popcorn mixture and toss to coat.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream oil, brown sugar and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beaten well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt, then add to mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by small teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If cookies flatten out too much, add a little more oatmeal.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bake for 1 hr at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar, vanilla and cocoa.
Add alternately water, flour and soda.
Bake at 375° until moist, about 30 minutes.

title: hot pie dip
directions: Mix together and bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Good served with crackers like Ritz, Sociables and such.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat in oil over high heat in skillet, leaving meat in coarse chunks. Add onions; reduce heat to medium and cook until onion is tender, but not brown. Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn and bouillon; bring to a boil. Stir in green peppers. Bring to a boil again. Stir. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: louise green's chocolate pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and milk with dry ingredients added first and last.
Beat after each addition.
The vanilla is added to the milk.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Cool in the pan for 15 minutes before turning out.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients into a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: preachers cookies
directions: Heat butter, sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper. Yield 3 dozen.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Dump ingredients into 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir in sugar, vanilla and almond chips.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Can substitute almond chips with butterscotch and the vanilla flavoring to almond.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix together, form loaf and cook at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Spicy/hot.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan until done.
While hot, punch holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Spread caramel topping over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: marvelous marshmallows
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in saucepan. Heat slowly, stirring, until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients. Cool slightly.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy and forms soft peaks. Pour into shallow dish; refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares to serve.

title: spinach with rice
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter and olive oil.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add spinach and rice.
When spinach is separated, reduce heat to medium; stir well. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: In a large skillet on medium-high heat, cook broccoli, zucchini, pepper, onion and basil in margarine until tender. Stir in tomatoes and mushrooms. Toss vegetable mixture with hot fettuccine.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves 5.

title: ginger creams
directions: Spread thin.
Makes one jelly roll pan or 3 coffee cake pans. Bake at 350°.

title: farina dumplings
directions: Beat ingredients together until batter is smooth.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drop from spoon into boiling stock.
Cook, covered, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan rolls
directions: In 2 round 9-inch cake pans, put 1/3 cup brown sugar, 3 tablespoons dark Karo and 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Mix and sprinkle nuts in each pan.

title: cream of cheese soup
directions: Boil carrots and onion in milk until carrots and onion are soft, being very careful not to burn.
Remove carrots and onion from milk.
Place milk in top of double boiler; thicken with butter and flour, which have been combined to a smooth paste. Stir constantly until thickened.
Add cheese; stir 3 minutes. Remove from fire.
Add beaten egg yolks, salt and pepper.

title: uncle jim's pasta sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil very slowly until translucent. Increase heat, stirring frequently until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Serve immediately over hot angel hair or vermicelli pasta.

title: grandma's vegetables
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to directions, then drain and set aside.
Combine cream cheese, milk, butter and onion salt; stir until cream cheese melts.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Add vegetables; heat well.

title: prune-apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together. Add prunes, apples and nuts.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until tested done. Cool 15 minutes and invert onto rack. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: mystery torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop crackers and nuts in blender. Gradually add sugar and baking powder. Add vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold them into blender.
Put mixture in a greased 8-inch pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes. Cool. Whip the cream with sugar to taste.
Spread on top.
Garnish with chocolate shavings.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar with 3 cups water in saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla beans; let stand until cold.

title: freezer bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours. Drain and rinse well.
Mix sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables, stirring, until sugar is dissolved and syrup is thin. Divide into plastic containers, cover tightly and freeze.
Pickles will be ready in 3 days.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Keeps 2 weeks.
Great on toast or crackers.

title: cranberry-pecan pie
directions: Stir together eggs, Karo syrup (light or dark), sugar and margarine until well blended.
Stir in cranberries, pecans and orange rind.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: yogurt cheese
directions: Stir together yogurt and herbs; then stir in Parmesan cheese. Set a small colander or funnel over a bowl.
Place a double layer of clean cheesecloth for cooking in the colander or funnel.
Spoon yogurt mixture into cheesecloth-lined colander or funnel; cover and place in refrigerator for at least 8 hours or overnight (allowing yogurt to drain).
Makes 8 (1 tablespoon) servings.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Make Jell-O as directed on package.
Soften cream cheese with a little pineapple juice to keep from lumping.
Mix in cherries, pineapple and nuts; pour into Jell-O which has just begun to set.
Mix well and chill.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Prepare topping:
In small bowl, mix brown sugar, walnuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Into large bowl, measure flour and remaining ingredients except remaining chocolate chips. With mixer at low speed, beat unti mixed, constantly scraping bowl.
Increase speed to high and beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Stir in reserved chocolate chips and pour into pan.
Spread topping over the batter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown together hamburger meat and bacon.
Add onions and garlic.
Drain excess liquid.
Add catsup, salt, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and beans.
Mix well.
Put in a large dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: amish jello tapioca
directions: When water is boiling, add tapioca.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes at a medium boil, stirring until it is clear and tapioca is soft.
Add cherry jello, sugar, fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple. Refrigerate.
Right before serving, fold in Cool
Whip.

title: cheese steak hoagie
directions: Cook Steak-umms, sliced onion and sliced mushrooms in 1 tablespoon margarine; drain. Put mixture back in the pan after draining. Put the cheese on top; heat until cheese is melted. Put mixture into rolls. Top with lettuce and sliced tomato. Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese in a blender or food processor until it is smooth and creamy.
Add green onions to the mixture or season with dried onion soup mix or your favorite seasonings.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Cook rice.
Combine beef, rice, Parmesan cheese, 1/2 can tomato sauce and corn.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Sprinkle each pepper with Parmesan cheese and evenly pour remaining tomato sauce over each pepper.
Cover with Saran Wrap and cook on High in microwave for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove wrap and sprinkle grated cheese on top. Re-cover and cook just long enough to melt cheese.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and slice thin.
Peel onions and slice. Alternate layers of potatoes and layers of onions.
Sprinkle onion layers with mixture of flour, salt and melted margarine (top layer must be potatoes).
Pour hot milk over all.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix together the meat, soup mix and eggs.
Use 3-minute quick oats to hold together (small amount).
Make small meatballs. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Place meatballs in dish.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers and enjoy!

title: barbecue kielbasa
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Brown kielbasa in frypan.
Combine kielbasa, onions and green pepper in large covered pot or crock-pot.
Add brown sugar, barbecue sauce and water.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until kielbasa is tender (longer, if in crock-pot).

title: party punch
directions: Mix lemon juice and orange juice as directed.
Dissolve cherry jelly in hot water.
Add sugar.
Add to mixture.
Add pineapple juice.
Just before serving add ginger ale.
Pour over chipped ice.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in powdered sugar.
Add oil and eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour; stir in vanilla.
Cover dough and chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: paste
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Add this to boiling water. Stir until mixed well and slightly thick.
Add food color of choice to cold water if colored paste is desired; cool.
Store in airtight container at room temperature.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, buttermilk and egg.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and soft butter.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a well-greased 4 x 8-inch loaf pan and two individual loaf pans. Bake the larger loaf for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Place carrots in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in croutons and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: frosty mountain cooler
directions: Combine concentrates and water.
Place ice cream and sherbet in bottom of punch bowl.
Break in small pieces with large spoon. Add juices.
Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 30 servings.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Put egg in large mixing bowl.
Beat with fork.
Mix in peanut butter, vanilla, salt and 1 cup sugar, then stir in other cup of sugar.
Cool.
Roll mixture into balls, then in chopped nuts. Place on waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: deep dish italian pie
directions: Pop out frozen pie crust from foil pan and place right side up on waxed paper to thaw, approximately 15 minutes. Set aside second pie crust.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Form dough into golf ball size.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix
the
ingredients and pour into pie shell.	Bake 30 to
35 minutes
at 350°.	This smells delicious while cooking and tastes delicious as well.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain.
Add taco mix and simmer about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and kidney beans.
Cook about 5 minutes and add crushed Fritos.
Stir.
Put in dish and add strips of cheese for garnish.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Add enough sweet milk to moisten.
Add 2 tablespoons Wesson oil.
Bake at 375°.
Bacon or hamburger can be added, also garlic salt.

title: ranch style cream potatoes
directions: Make your creamed potatoes as you normally do.
Add dressing mix to your potatoes while mixing.

title: boiled chocolate icing
directions: Mix and boil for 2 minutes. Add vanilla and beat. Let cool until thicken.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients in order listed.
Spoon mixture into 18 to 20 foil baking cups in muffin pans.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: pat a pie crust
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and sugar in pie pan.
Whip together the milk and oil and pour over flour mixture.
Mix together in pie pan with fork until flour is completely dampened. Shape into pie pan with fingers.
Fill as is or bake, then fill. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until light brown).

title: luau pork tenderloin
directions: Combine honey, soy sauce, brown sugar, prepared mustard and vinegar in a shallow pan.
Roll pork tenderloins in mixture; marinate 1 hour, turning once or twice.
Set oven at 350°.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Stir
shortening
to	soften;
gradually
add
sugar, creaming until light.
Add	eggs; beat until light and fluffy. Sift together
dry	ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with
applesauce,
beating after each addition; stir in nuts.
Pour into
paper-lined
x
5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a
moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour.
While still warm, top with
sugar
glaze; mix 1/2 cup sifted confectioners sugar and 1 tablespoon water.

title: pa. dutch funnel cakes
directions: Beat egg; add milk.
Add salt, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into funnel, holding finger over the bottom.
Swirl batter into fry pan of hot oil, from center out.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Top with confectioners sugar.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven
to
Divide apples in 2 custard cups. Sprinkle
water
over
apples.
Mix
other	ingredients
until crumbly
and sprinkle over apples.	Bake, uncovered, until the topping is	light
brown
and apples are tender, 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 2 servings.

title: ground beef sauerbraten
directions: Lightly brown beef in hot skillet; add onion and salt and continue cooking until onion is tender (about 5 minutes).
Add water, vinegar and ginger.
Move meat mixture to sides of skillet. Add vegetables and bring to a full boil over medium heat, separating vegetables
with fork.
Stir until sauce cubes are blended.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 minutes.
If desired, serve over cooked noodles.
Makes 3 servings.

title: low-fat bacon, lettuce and tomato sandwich
directions: Spread	mayonnaise
on	bread.	Sprinkle on bacon bits. Add lettuce and tomatoes.
Less than 150 calories.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine and press in 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Mix sugar, water and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Add jello and mix until dissolved.
When a little cool, pour over berries and chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: stewed corn
directions: In a heavy skillet or Dutch oven, fry the bacon until crisp. Remove and drain on paper towel.
Saute in bacon drippings the onion, celery and bell pepper until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and a little water (about 2 ounces).
Add parsley, basil, sugar, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes. Add creamed corn and 1/2 can water. Stir in crumbled bacon.
Blend well and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: best cole slaw
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: flan sol y sombra(sun and shadow custard; low-fat)
directions: Blend eggs, honey and salt.
Add remaining ingredients except nutmeg.
Blend well.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; pour in mixture and sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Set dish in a pan of warm water and bake in preheated very slow oven (250°) for 2 hours or until firm.
Cool; chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crowd pleasing potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl.
Separate eggs.
Chop whites and add to potatoes with onion and celery.
Toss gently.
In another bowl, mash yolks with salad dressing, cream, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Pour over potatoes and stir to coat.
Garnish with parsley.
Cover and chill.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: coconut pies
directions: Grease pans.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Knife will come clean when done.
Don't overbake.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch squares.
Fry in a bit of butter sprinkled with a bit of onion soup mix.
After completely fried add a large can of mushroom soup and simmer for approximately 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: microwave peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in square glass Pyrex dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Nuke uncovered on high for 6 minutes.
Rotate dish half a turn and nuke another 4-6 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Conventional oven:
30-35 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: best ever pancakes
directions: Sift flour before measuring, then resift with sugar, salt, baking powder and soda.
Beat eggs, then mix with buttermilk. Combine the dry and liquid ingredients with a few quick strokes, then add melted butter.
Mix ingredients well, but with as few strokes as possible.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake on hot griddle until brown.
Serves:
20 (4-inch cakes).

title: creamy dill dip
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Put into serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Will keep for 2 weeks.
Serve with cherry tomatoes, carrots, celery, etc.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk and 3/4 cup melted butter.
In double boiler, melt caramels and 1/4 cup evaporated milk.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes until done (firm).
Pour caramel mixture over and spread.
Pour chopped pecans and chocolate chips over mixture.
Pour remainder of cake mixture over it.
Bake 10 minutes.
Better if stands for 24 hours.

title: lentil spaghetti sauce(no cholesterol)
directions: Saute in olive oil the chopped onions, garlic and tomatoes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.

title: greatest pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco until mealy; add water.
Mix, then refrigerate for several hours.
Roll out.
This is for a 2 crust pie.
Put in a 9-inch pan and trim excess off the edges.
Bake at 375° to 400° until golden brown.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix in the order given and pour into 2 baked pie shells; chill.
Freezes well.

title: three bean apple salad
directions: In a serving bowl, combine all ingredients except radishes. Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, to blend flavors.
Just before serving, add radishes and toss.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Pour over baked crust and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: For jellied cranberry sauce:
Bring water and cranberries to a boil; boil for five minutes.
Put mixture through strainer or food mill.
Stir in sugar and return to boil; remove from heat.
Pour into mold or other container; lay waxed paper directly on surface to prevent formation of skin; cool slightly and refrigerate.

title: savory tomato soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend flour in.
Add remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thick.
Reduce heat; cook slowly for approximately 20 minutes.
Garnish with bacon.
Serves 2.

title: hot parmesan puffs
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayo, onion, parmesan, cheese, and pepper. Cut bread in squares or rounds and trim crust and bake at 300° for 5 minutes to harden.
Spread mixture on bread.
Sprinkle with parmesan and paprika, (freeze like this) or broil until puffy and golden brown on top, watch closely.

title: super zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Combine cream, flour, salt, pepper, paprika, garlic powder and onion.
Layer potatoes, creamer mix and butter alternately in casserole dish.
Pour boiling water over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take meat off chicken bones and place in greased dish.
In bowl, mix celery soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Mix Stove Top stuffing with 2 cups of chicken broth and spread over chicken. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swiss banana cake
directions: *To sour milk, add enough milk to 1 teaspoon vinegar to make 1/3 cup.
Prepare ahead and let stand.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Use any hot roll recipe.
Add a little flour to make dough stiff.
After shaping, let rise not quite double.
Bake 30 minutes in a 275° oven.
Cool and store in airtight bags.
Can store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Drain oranges; save syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Pour into gelatin; mix and chill until slightly thickened.
blend in sherbet; beat with electric beater until well blended.
Place mandarin oranges into 1-quart mold.
Add gelatin mixture; chill until firm.
Serves 4.

title: fruited tea(from stuffed goose - tullahoma, tn)
directions: Use gallon container.
Mix ingredients and enough water to fill the container.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Place egg yolks, pumpkin, sugar, vanilla, salt and spices in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until it begins to thicken.
Mix unflavored gelatin with cold water.
Dissolve gelatin in hot pumpkin.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Fold into chilled pumpkin.
Pour into baked crust.
Keep refrigerated until serving.

title: breakfast bundt cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients for 3 minutes, then mix together sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour a little batter in bottom of pan.
Then add the sugar mixed with cinnamon and sprinkle with nuts.
Pour rest of batter over that.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes (check for doneness in 35 minutes).

title: tallareni
directions: Fry onion in butter and brown meat.
Add soup and water; bring to full boil.
Add cooked noodles, corn, mushrooms, olives and all seasonings.
Pour in greased casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: meat and tater pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix; roll out for 2-crust 9-inch pie.
Line pie plate with one crust.
Combine meat, milk, soup mix, pepper and allspice.
Lightly pat into pastry-lined pie plate.
Top with potatoes.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cut design in top pastry.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: tante helga's klat cookies
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add egg; set aside. Blend remaining dry ingredients.
Slowly add to sugar mixture.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: dump cake ii
directions: Do not grease pan!
Pour pineapple and peach pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
"Dump" dry cake mix over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: millet waffles
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender and blend on high for 2 to 3 minutes (may need to do 1/2 at a time).
Cook on waffle iron. They cook slowly, so allow more time than for regular waffles.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, onion and egg.
Then beat in milk or water.
Drop from spoon into hot oil where fish was cooked.
Done when golden brown.

title: chicken dish
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow pan.
Put salt, pepper and parsley
on
chicken.
Add	1 can creamy chicken mushroom soup (undiluted)
on chicken.
Bake 30 minutes.	Add slice or more
of cheese
on	each
piece and can of drained mushrooms (optional). Heat until cheese melts.
Bake at 350°.

title: fried potato patties
directions: Squeeze potatoes between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine all ingredients, except vegetable oil, stirring well.
Drop 1/4 cup of potato mixture at a time into 1/8-inch hot oil; press into 3-inch rounds with the back of a fork.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: deep dish brownies from scratch
directions: In a medium bowl blend melted margarine, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs; beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chips.
Spread into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: governor whitman's favorite recipe (raspberry chicken)
directions: In a blender, place 2 cups of raspberries, the corn syrup and the lemon juice; cover and blend on high until smooth.
In a small saucepan, stir together the cornstarch, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in the raspberry mixture until smooth.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil for 1 minute.
Arrange chicken and remaining raspberries in a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: country scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and ham in a lightly greased crock-pot. In a small bowl, combine the gravy mix, soup and water. Whisk until combined. Pour gravy mixture over the potatoes. Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours. Top with cheese during last 30 minutes.

title: banana boats
directions: Slice banana in half lengthwise.
Fill with chocolate chips. Wrap in foil.
Lay on hot coals for several minutes.
Very yummy!

title: golden cornbread
directions: Preheat oven 425°F. oven. Grease and flour 9 x 9 inch pan. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into pan and bake for 20 -25 minutes.

title: oven pancake
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Mix flour, milk and eggs together. Add dash of nutmeg.
Pour into skillet and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or brown sugar.
Serve with jam or syrup.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash, cut tops from peppers and remove seeds.
In large bowl mix ground beef, okra, corn, tomatoes, onion, rice, pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Stuff peppers.
Place in large pan, cover with foil.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 2 hours or until well done.
Baste peppers several times with the broth that comes from peppers. Cover with tomato sauce or catsup 30 minutes before removing from oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter and mix until smooth (use more peanut butter if desired). Roll mixture into small balls and refrigerate overnight.
Melt chips, dip balls and place on aluminum foil to dry.

title: honey roasted fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut and peel oranges and grapefruit. Cut into segments.
Save juices.
Set aside.
Peel pineapple; cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Core center and cut into 8 slices in quarters.
Peel bananas.
Halve crosswise, then lengthwise.
Toss in bowl with lemon juice.
Arrange in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange pineapple, overlapping the pieces slightly.
Next, a row of orange segments, followed by grapefruit and oranges, then finish with bananas.
Can be made ahead of time to this point and refrigerated.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Drizzle honey over top, then brown sugar.
Bake 30 minutes, basting twice with any pan juices.
Garnish with mint.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve gelatine in tablespoon cold water; add to boiling water and cool.
Take cranberries through grinder (fine); also grind 1 whole orange (juice of 1 orange).
Mix thoroughly with the gelatine and add orange juice, sugar and nut meats.
Place in refrigerator to set up.
Will keep 6 months in freezer.
Put in sealed jars.

title: poor mans lobster tail
directions: Note:
One pound of haddock fillets is enough for 2 people.

title: curry
directions: In a large skillet, fry onions and meat in 3 Tbsp. oil.
Add vegetables and stir fry for 5 minutes.
Add 3 c. water and bring to a boil.
Break curry mix into pieces and stir in till dissolved.
Bring to a simmer, cover and stir occasionally.
Cook and stir till desired consistency.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 cups.

title: veggies-pasta poupouri
directions: Take your favorite pasta.
We like bow ties.
Put pasta water on to boil.
As you wait for the water to boil, check refrigerator; what fresh vegetables are available.
Pick one or a handful of every color.
We generally find options like carrots, green beans or pepper, squash.
Leftovers are okay, too, but if you use corn, remove from cob.
Check freezer if your fresh veggies' color selection is low; we've used frozen corn and peas.
If using any frozen vegetables, set aside on counter to defrost.
Together, you want about 3 cups of vegetables once you cut up larger items, chunks or slices, nothing too thick.
Get out the wok and add about 2 tablespoons of oil.
Heat until it sizzles on medium-high heat. By now, you should be able to put on the pasta.
In the wok, stir-fry the fresh vegetables.
If you are using some frozen, make sure they are defrosted/drained; pat with paper towel before you add them to the wok.
When pasta is cooked and drained, immediately toss with egg (it will cook from the heat of the pasta) and several pats of butter.
Gently toss pasta with cooked vegetables; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: hot potato salad for 100
directions: In a large skillet fry bacon until crisp; remove to paper towels to drain.
Add flour to drippings.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
In a large kettle, heat vinegar, water and sugar to boiling.
Gradually add flour mixture; cook and stir until thickened.
Add salt, pepper, onion and pickles.
Mix well. Place hot potatoes in serving pans.
Divide sauce among pans and stir to coat.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 100 or makes 7 gallons.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Mix and set aside.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Mix instant pudding using milk.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter to pudding mixture.
Add 1/2 cup Dream Whip to peanut butter-pudding mixture. Put 1/2 of the peanut butter crumbs in bottom of baked pie shell (save rest for top).
Put pudding mixture on top of crumbs in shell.
Top with remaining Dream Whip and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: tangy yellow squash
directions: Combine the squash, onion, green pepper and celery in a large mixing bowl; toss lightly.
Combine wine vinegar, salt, pepper, salad oil, cider vinegar and garlic; stir well.
Spoon over vegetables.
Chill about 12 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: granny soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Place in large boiler.
Cut onion and add to potatoes.
Cook until near tender. Add tomatoes and corned beef.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve with corn bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole dish.
Mix soup with milk.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese.
Mix Bisquick with butter until crumbly.
Put over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown on top and cheese is bubbly.
(Freezes very well before or after cooking.)

title: salsa chicken melt
directions: Top slice of bread with cheese, salsa, chicken and second slice of bread. Spread sandwich with margarine.
Cook in skillet on medium heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: hand-me down chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and vanilla and beat 1 minute. Mix together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured).

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Leave overnight.
Next day, add the last 3 ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes, until it breaks on top in angel food cake pan.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Rub 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix cake mix (dry) and 1 egg.
Melt butter.
Pour melted butter in with cake mix.
Spread mix evenly throughout
pan.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour mix over crust (cake mix).
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease cake pan.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together; set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, milk, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Stir well; pour into pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting, if desired.

title: peanut butter loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in peanut butter with a fork. Add egg and milk.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted near middle comes out clean.
Makes approximately 18 slices.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil or butter a small or standard loaf pan.
In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and beer.
Mix with
a wooden spoon until well blended and sticky, about 1 minute.
Pour dough into prepared pan and bake for 30 minutes. Remove the bread from the oven and pour the melted butter over the top. Bake for 30 more minutes until lightly browned on top.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, corn, onions, cheese and olives in a large mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans in well buttered casserole or baking dish. Spread soup evenly over beans, then arrange onion rings on top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven until bubbly.
Two cups crushed potato chips may be substituted for onion rings, if desired. Yields 4 servings.

title: double quick batter buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar, salt, eggs and butter. Beat in flour.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Stir down and spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown on top.

title: microwave never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a 2-quart measuring cup.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Bring next 4 ingredients to boil in a saucepan.
While this mixture is still boiling, pour over the dry ingredients.
Mix well and add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a large pan, greased and floured. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Start icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add all ingredients listed.
Place in your prettiest dish and you can add cherries on top for more color, if desired.
Easy and delicious.
Better when left overnight in refrigerator.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple, add jello to pineapple.
Add cottage cheese, stir in Cool Whip.
Drain oranges and set aside a few for garnishing.
Add oranges to mixture.
Garnish with a few oranges on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a crack appears in the middle of loaves.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and line with tortillas, broken into bite size pieces.
Put chicken (also bite size pieces) on top. Mix soups, tomatoes and onions.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Form 1-inch balls from meat, egg, bread crumbs and seasoning. In skillet, combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Simmer, stirring until smooth.
Add meatballs. Simmer 1 hour.
Serve hot. Makes 25 to 30 meatballs.

title: hot and spicy party mix
directions: Cheerios and pretzels may be added.

title: sausage and pepper dish
directions: Cut frozen sausage into slices abut 1/4 inch in size.
Put into a roasting pan with oil and garlic.
Slice the green peppers; add to sausage.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° until sausage and peppers are almost cooked.
Keep on stirring the ingredients so they don't stick together as sausage can do if not stirred.
When almost cooked, add the crushed tomatoes and cover.
Cook for about 1 hour more, until all ingredients are well cooked.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and French dressing in a bowl.
Place onion and carrots in the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover chicken in sauce and place on vegetables.
Use remaining sauce to baste chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Will serve 4 to 6 people.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water and add to the cranberry and sugar mixture.
Add crushed pineapple, juice included.
Add the orange juice and the chopped nuts; mix well.
Congeal in the refrigerator overnight.

title: double corn muffins
directions: Combine corn, cheese, sour cream, milk, egg and sugar until well mixed.
Spray nonstick cooking spray directly on chopped onion and microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Add to corn mixture.
Stir in cornmeal and blend well.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 to almost full. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries the night before serving.
Stir in marshmallows, sugar and pineapple.
Day of serving add apples and nuts.
Last, fold in whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all together.
Bake in a buttered casserole for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: deluxe fajita nachos
directions: In medium skillet combine chicken, fajita spices and water; blend well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer.
In large shallow ovenproof platter arrange chips, top with chicken and cheese and place under broiler to melt cheese.
Top with tomatoes, olives and green onions.
Add desired amount of salsa.

title: barbecue
directions: Bake shoulder until done, about 2 hours at 300°.
Then chop up meat.
Add vinegar, red pepper and salt to taste.
Mix up the meat with the ingredients.
Put back in the oven until golden brown.

title: grandmother's chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in water. Mix until smooth (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: bark cookies
directions: Melt bark in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 200° oven.
Bark will melt faster if you cut into small chunks.
Stir occasionally.
When melted, stir in rest of ingredients, combining thoroughly and quickly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Can use Froot Loops and more cereal, if desired.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper (use all salt and pepper).
Drain vegetables and put in large bowl with green pepper and red onion.
Pour oil mixture over vegetables and chill overnight.
Pour off oil mixture before serving.

title: fruit balls
directions: Melt butter; add dates. Cream sugar and eggs and add to dates and butter mixture. Cook on low until thick. Keep it stirred. Stir constantly. Take off heat and let it cool. Add Rice Krispies, fruit, nuts and flavoring. Roll into balls and then roll in coconut. Store in a cool place or freeze. Makes about 50.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in half and half and 1 tablespoon oil.
Gradually add boiling water, stirring until batter is the consistency of grits.
Pour oil to a depth of 1/2-inch into large heavy skillet (cast-iron); place over medium-high heat.
Scoop batter into a 1/4-cup measure; drop into hot oil and fry in batches 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with softened butter.
Makes approximately 1 dozen.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat all together.
Drop by tablespoon into hot deep fat. Brown as much as needed.
Drain in paper towel.
Serve with butter, syrup and jelly or as is.

title: mother's angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 1/2 cup sugar together 4 times.
Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavorings until foamy. Gradually add 1 1/3 cups sugar in 4 additions, beating well between additions.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in flour and sugar mixture in 4 additions.
Gently spoon into ungreased tube pan. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn upside down to cool.

title: plum pudding(no bake)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 pint of water (hot).
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Remove chicken wing tips; discard.
Cut wings in half through joint.
In large bowl, stir together soy sauce and remaining ingredients.
Add chicken and toss until coated well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove wings from marinade and place in a single layer in 2 jelly roll pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until tender, brushing twice with marinade.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix hot milk, butter, sugar and salt in a bowl and let cool to lukewarm.
Stir the yeast into 1/4 cup warm water and let it stand for 5 minutes to dissolve.
Add the dissolved yeast and 2 cups of the flour to the first mixture.
Stir fast and add enough of the remaining flour so that the dough pulls away from the sides of the bowl.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board.
Knead for a minute or two and let rest for 10 minutes.
Resume kneading until smooth and elastic.
Put in a buttered bowl.
Cover and let rise until it doubles in size.
Punch down and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in 1/2 inch strips.
Put on buttered cookie sheets.
Cover and let rise.
Brush with egg white.
Cook 30 minutes.
Sprinkle them with coarse salt before baking.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll pizza crust on greased cookie sheet; bake until lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread over pizza crust.
Sprinkle onions and peppers over pizza.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Pat down, if needed.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Cut and you are ready to eat.

title: fat-free bean pole stew
directions: Place tomatoes with their juice in a large
soup kettle.
Add undrained beans and all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy; stir in vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add creamed mixture alternately with milk and coconut milk.
Stir in coconut; fold in egg whites.
Turn into two greased paper-lined cake pans.
Bake at 365° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add shrimp (it is better if shrimp are thawed out).
Add all other ingredients.
(Drain water and juice of olives and pimentos.)

title: dilled brussels sprouts
directions: Wash Brussels sprouts thoroughly, discarding any wilted outer leaves, then trim the stems and cut an X in the base of each. Steam them over boiling water for about 10 minutes or until just tender.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over the Brussels sprouts.
Serve hot or well chilled.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: On day before serving, cook, mash and whip potatoes with cheese and sour cream.
Add garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, dot with big dots of butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400°, covered, for 40 to 50 minutes.
Leave mixture at least one-inch from top since it grows.
Serves 10 people.

title: low-fat dip
directions: Place cheesecloth or coffee filters in a colander and pour yogurt into it to drain.
Let yogurt drain for at least 45 minutes. After yogurt drains, it will have a texture between sour cream and cream cheese.
The longer you allow it to drain, the more like cream cheese it becomes.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix together in a punch bowl and serve.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: In buttered 9-inch square baking dish, layer broccoli, chicken, bread crumbs and cheese.
In medium bowl, combine gravy, milk and pepper; pour over chicken-broccoli mixture.
Bake in 357° oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: company beef oriental
directions: Cook hamburg, onion and garlic until brown.
Drain fat.
Add soy sauce, cornstarch, molasses, bouillon, water and juice from oranges.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pea pods, water chestnuts (drained) and bamboo shoots (drained).
Heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Add oranges and heat 5 minutes more.
Serve over hot rice.

title: banana cake
directions: Place cake mix in large bowl.
Stir in baking soda, buttermilk, eggs and bananas.
Bake as directed on box.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; add flour.
Gradually add water; stir until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes.
Boil and pour over sliced, cooked potatoes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat egg yolks; add lemon juice.
Add flour and sugar mixed before adding to egg and lemon juice.
Add salt, butter and fruit juice but be sure to keep stirring all the time.
Keeps quite a while in refrigerator.
When cool, add to whipping cream as much as you need.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and cream until it reaches the soft-ball stage. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful on wax paper to cool.

title: creme de menthe crepe
directions: Soak gelatin in water in a cup until softened.
Place in pan of hot water and heat until it dissolves.
Cool to lukewarm.
In small bowl, combine milk, sugar, creme de menthe, heavy cream, food coloring, mint flavoring and salt.
Beat until thickened. Gradually, add gelatin, mixing thoroughly.
Set aside 1 tablespoon shaved chocolate and fold remainder into cream mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: ceuiche
directions: Juice limes.
Cut crab, shrimp and onions to dip size.
Cut up peppers and cilantro into small pieces.
(Seed peppers if necessary).
Add oregano and salsa to make dip-like mixture.
Let sit 24 hours for best taste.
Use with tortilla chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: With electric mixer, cream all items together.
Refrigerate until firm.
Make 1 large or 2 medium balls; roll in chopped nuts and parsley.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
May be frozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients and mix until well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches. Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour dough into pan.
Pour peaches on top (do not stir, dough will rise to top to form crust).
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: vegetarian meatless spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute all vegetables in large pan with 1/4 cup olive oil 5 to 7 minutes; add tomatoes and all spices and simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Serve over a good semolina or spinach pasta and sprinkle generously with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve with a large green salad and garlic bread.
Buon appetito.

title: chicken casserole iv
directions: Put all in oiled casserole, except chips and cheese.
May be made hours ahead or night before and kept in refrigerator.
Before baking, put crushed potato chips and grated cheese on top.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together the soup, milk, and pepper.
Pour over the potatoes and onion in greased casserole pan.
Add butter on top. Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour, covered.
Then uncover for 15 minutes more until potatoes are done.

title: ham pie
directions: In a saucepan, saute broccoli, bell pepper, mushrooms, onion, and garlic in oil until tender.
Sprinkle half of the ham and cheese into the pie crust.
Cover with the vegetables and the remaining ham and cheese.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix pineapple juice, soy sauce, sherry or stock, garlic, parsley and pepper.
Marinate chicken breasts for 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Grill chicken.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken, broccoli and cheese mixture.
Top with croutons and bake at 350° until heated through and bubbly.

title: corn souffle
directions: Bake in casserole dish at 350° or until golden brown.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients using enough cans undiluted mushroom soup to make mixture quite wet.
Bake 30 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove lid last 5 minutes. Serve with rye crackers.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 small pans.
Beat flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar, sour cream, oil, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs for 50 strokes. Stir in nuts and berries.
Pour in pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: blueberry-banana muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or lightly grease bottoms only with no-stick cooking spray.
Combine wheat germ, flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add combined milk, oil, egg and banana; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in blueberries.
Fill prepared muffin cups almost full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or store tightly wrapped in freezer.
To reheat, microwave at High 30 seconds per muffin.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Add enough flour to make dough so it can be rolled out like biscuits.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread the pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Scatter dry cake mix in a layer over the filling.
Drop slices of margarine over the cake mix.
Scatter nuts and coconut on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add flour.
Put in a 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Poke holes in top with fork.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put directly into muffin tins or use paper liners.
Bake at 350°F 15-20 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Note: You may also use cubed ham, green pepper, black olives or celery.

title: golden oven fried chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings in a large bowl. Dip chicken in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place on buttered baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to an hour.
May be refrigerated after cooking.

title: laura's country dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender for a few minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into a quiche pan and bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: chicken little
directions: Sprinkle
chicken
with salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat oil in	skillet;
brown both sides of chicken for 20 minutes. Add lemon
juice,
water
and
herbs.
Cover
and cook for 10 minutes; add
vegetables.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes more or until tender.
Serves 6 at 225 calories.

title: wheat germ muffins(from:  better homes and gardens magazine)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, wheat germ and sugar.
In another bowl, combine egg, water, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat smooth with rotary beater.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Do not overbeat.)
Spoon batter into greased or lined muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: pineapple hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat broiler.
Break joints of chicken.
Brush chicken with oil; season with salt and pepper.
Place skin side down.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Turn; broil 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Slice steak across grain into 1/4-inch strips.
Peel and chop garlic.
Heat to high a wok or large skillet.
When hot, add the oil, meat strips and garlic.
Cover and stir for about 3 minutes. Dice onion and cut pepper into strips.
Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Drain mushrooms and add these to wok.
Add soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Continue cooking and stirring for approximately 5 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; let cool.
Add sour cream, margarine, soup and dressing (save a little dressing for top of casserole).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: yogurt dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with fresh vegetables or fruit.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Mix both sugars, margarine and egg in large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt (dough will be stiff).
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: clinton cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop batter by well rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes before placing on wire rack. Makes 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peach ice cream
directions: I use a blender for the peaches.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Toss gently before serving.

title: creamy peach pudding
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt in large saucepan.
Combine milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Stir in peaches.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Best when served warm.

title: cocktail sausage(may sound strange, but always a hit at parties!)
directions: Heat sausages in microwave or oven according to package directions.
Melt jelly over low heat in saucepan, stirring constantly.
When jelly has become liquid, slowly add mustard, stirring until sauce is smooth and creamy.
Add sausages to sauce and serve in chafing dish to keep warm.
Use toothpicks to serve.

title: chocolate easter eggs
directions: For coconut eggs, mix coconut, Marshmallow Fluff, 1/2 pound butter and 1/2 pound 10x sugar.
Refrigerate for 3 to 5 hours. Roll out eggs in various sizes.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler or microwave.
Do not overcook!
Dip eggs in chocolate. Place on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: berry cobbler(or peach)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place
berries in a greased 2 quart baking
dish
and stir in cinnamon, lemon juice and half the sugar.
Sift
together
flour,
baking
powder
and salt. Combine the
eggs, milk, oleo, vanilla and remaining half cup of
sugar. Combine
the dry ingredients with the wet and beat just
until lumps
are gone.
Pour over the fruit and bake an hour, uncovered, or until the cake pulls in from the sides of the
pan. Serve
with
natural
vanilla
ice cream or yogurt. Serves 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Over low heat melt caramels, margarine and milk.
Pour over top of baked cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Cover with remaining cake mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine broccoli, corn, egg, 1/4 cup cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons butter, onion, salt and pepper in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter atop casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and cream.
Stir until smooth. Pour into an 8-inch square pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Stir in nuts and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion; pour off any grease; add salt and pepper.
Add soup and water and simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.
Noodles can be served in meat or separate.

title: slow-cook beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch pieces; arrange in greased 5-quart casserole with lid.
Cut carrots, celery and potatoes in bite-size pieces.
Layer over beef.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, sugar and tapioca.
Pour tomato sauce, tomatoes and wine over top.
Bake covered at 275° for 6 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except pecans and crackers.
Let set in refrigerator about 2 days in plastic bowl.
Take out.
Roll into ball.
Roll into pecans.
Serve with toasted butter crackers.

title: fried fish fillet
directions: Use cast-iron pan with Crisco a quarter inch deep.
Salt and pepper fish and flour.
Make sure the pan is hot (not too hot) and fry skin up first.
Fry until flour on top is gone and turn.
Best way to enjoy fried fish.

title: buttered crunch
directions: Melt morsels over hot water. Remove from heat and stir in chow mein noodles and salted peanuts. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Let stand 20 minutes at room temperature. Makes about 4 dozen pieces.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Mix sugar, water, shortening, raisins, spices and salt together.
Boil 3 minutes. Cool.
Dissolve soda in water and add to sugar mixture. Blend in flour, baking powder and nuts.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut in bars. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp and grind up; mix together with the rest of the ingredients.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Spread mayo over onions, sealing to edge of bowl.
Top with sour cream.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with bacon and shredded cheese, if desired.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Put
soup,
wine
and
milk in a baking dish.
Stir and place onions
and
chicken in the mixture.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Trim off ends of zucchini and cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers.
Place shells in shallow pan.	Dice pulp; set aside. Brown meat, garlic and onion.
Stir in pulp, parsley, salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and egg.
Spoon into shells and top with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
An easy way to use up zucchini.

title: ruth's 2-flavor fudge
directions: Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in 1 cup walnuts, chopped, and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
About 2 1/2 pounds.

title: parmesan potatoes
