directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten the potatoes with water and shake a few pieces at a time in the bag, coating them well.
Place in melted oleo and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: potato gourmet
directions: Melt cheese and butter in a pan.
Dice potatoes.
Put potatoes, cheese mixture, sour cream and onions into a casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper; mix.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over cake mix and swirl it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Chill milk thoroughly before adding above mixture.
When frozen in the freezer to a mush stage, add 1 pint of cream, whipped.
Finish freezing.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, almond and lemon extracts.
Fold in flour and milk alternately.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for about 1 hour or until cake tests done with a dry toothpick.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add soft margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Then stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into 2 pie shells. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: papier-mache
directions: Tear sheets of newspaper into strips about 1-inch wide, tearing down from the fold.
To make papier-mache paste, put the flour in a large bowl.
Add water, a little at a time, stirring until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Dip strips of paper into the paste.
Paste the strips in all directions over the object you want to cover.
Set your papier-mache object in a warm place to dry.
(This may take several days.)
When it has dried completely, paint colorful design on it with tempera paint.

title: jam bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder; gradually add to margarine mixture.
Add coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.

title: corny coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lettuce.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Serves 4.

title: crispy corny baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove skin and fat from chicken; season with paprika and pepper.
Dip in milk and roll in crumbs. Place in greased pan making sure pieces do not touch.
Bake for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: poppy's spanish chicken and rice
directions: Rinse and dry chicken.
Heat oil in skillet until haze forms above it.
Reduce heat and brown chicken well on all sides; remove form pan, drizzle with sherry.
Add vegetables to oil; cook until limp.
Add rice and saute until opaque and coated with oil.
Add chicken broth and seasonings, return to boil.
Pour rice mixture into 2 1/2-quart greased casserole; top with browned chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes with cheese sprinkled on top.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Stir and let stand overnight.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: hot chocolate
directions: In covered micro-cooker combine chocolate morsels and milk. Microwave on HIGH 3 minutes; whisk using 10 inch whisk until thoroughly blended.
Add instant chocolate mix; whisk until combined.
Microwave on HIGH 2 - 2 1/2 minutes or until hot.
Pour into mugs; top each serving with miniature marshmallows, if desired.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings (approx. 3 cups).

title: creole cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients for cake.
Pour into ungreased pan (approximately 13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Ice while still warm.

title: bishop bread
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt, flour, baking powder and cherry juice.
Add nuts, dates, cherries (whole) and chocolate bar pieces.
Line bread pans with wax paper prior to putting batter in.
Cover with heavy brown paper while baking.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: hearty chicken loaf with whole wheat crumbs
directions: Position rack in middle of oven and preheat to 400°.
Spread bread crumbs in shallow metal pan (like cake tin) and toast them in oven, stirring often, until lightly browned (10 minutes).
Cool to room temperature.
Lower oven temperature to 350°.

title: fried apple pie
directions: Put apples in a pan and cover with water.
Cook until apples are good and tender, approximately 1 hour.
Drain excess water off apples.
Mix the rest of the ingredients with the apples.
Put in refrigerator until cold.
Roll dough out about the size of a saucer.
Put 2 tablespoons apple mixture to one side of the dough. Then cover with the other half.
Press down edges with a floured fork.
Place on waxed paper that is sprinkled with flour.
Make all pies.
Fry in iron skillet in hot shortening.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 18.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and put in an airtight container.
When using, mix 2 tablespoons to a cup of hot water.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrot, onion, parsley flakes, seasonings and bouillon cube.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add milk and flour together, then add to vegetables. Cook until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: frozen fruit cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into blender in two batches.
Pour into muffin tins lined with foil cupcake liners. Place in freezer on a flat surface.
Freeze and store in plastic bag.
Let thaw 2 or 3 minutes before serving.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into patties.
Fry in small amount of oil.

title: marinade for flank steak
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over flank steak.
Marinate 8 hours or more, turning meat periodically.
Strain onions out of marinade while cooking steak.
Cut cooked steak into narrow strips and serve with marinade.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until marshmallows are melted. Cool.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet chocolate frosting
directions: Heat half and half in saucepan until bubbles form, remove from heat. Add to butter and cocoa, 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, syrup, and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Add remaining powdered sugar, beating until smooth.

title: ginny's tomato-shrimp casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Lower heat. Stir flour into drippings, cooking until brown 12 to 15 minutes. Stir in onion, red and green peppers, garlic, salt, pepper, red pepper and thyme.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Gradually add broth, okra, tomatoes and green onions.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in peeled, cleaned, raw shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Add bacon.
Serve on rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger and taco mix.
Set aside to cool.
Crush in Doritos.
Mix all chopped lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and hamburger together.
Add French dressing last, not too far from serving, about 1/2 hour.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Drain fruit; mix cornstarch and ginger.
Add to liquid and cook until clear.
Add fruit and spread in an 8-inch baking dish. Slice banana over fruit.
Combine oats and melted butter. Sprinkle over fruit mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy low-fat cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease 9 inch pie plate. Cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown. Drain; stir in salt. Spread into pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese. Stir remaining ingredients in bowl until blended. Pour into pie plate. Bake for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oleo.
Add Cheez Whiz and undiluted soup.
Heat until smooth.
Add milk and salt.
Cook broccoli; put rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Add cooked broccoli on top.
Cover with soup mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add all ingredients, but nuts and oats; beat well.
Add nuts and oats.
Form in rolls and chill at least 45 minutes in refrigerator.
Slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pastor miller's strawberry pie in the eye
directions: Cover pastor up really, really, really good, then take aim and let it go.
Boy, is that good or what?

title: alyson's texan favorite boneless beef brisket
directions: Cover tightly and marinate overnight.
Place in a covered pan and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Uncover and drain.
Bake 1 hour longer.
Slice and serve.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden; set aside.
Roll meat in flour.
Cook until brown.
Saute in remaining butter.
Place in pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium for about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dice up all vegetables; add vinegar, sugar, oil and water. Put
a dash of salt and pepper, if desired. Serve on lettuce.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat well. Spoon into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until it comes away from sides of pan.

title: broiled haddock
directions: Butter or grease a shallow, oven glass baking dish, then arrange the fish on it.
Brush each fillet with some of the melted butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil about 2 inches from the heat until lightly browned and flaky (never turn fish while broiling).

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square baking dish (8 x 8-inch). Cook and drain ground beef.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, onions and cheese in separate dish; set aside.
Mix Bisquick and water and pat into pan and press 1/2 inch up sides.
Layer the ground beef, sliced tomatoes, green pepper and sour cream mixture on top. Sprinkle with a little paprika.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer sugar, water and instant coffee for 45 minutes.
Cool. Add vanilla and
vodka.
Makes 2 (1/2 fifths).

title: coney sauce
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and celery in the water until celery is cooked.
Add catsup, chili powder, salt, pepper and sugar; cook a little longer.
Delicious on hot dogs.

title: honey sandwich bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix well with graham flour, bran and nuts.
Beat eggs and add milk and honey. Add to dry ingredients and mix only enough to dampen all the flour.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: homesteader's sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in enough water to cover till tender.
Peel and mash, add all other ingredients.
Flavor with lemon or nutmeg and bake in pie shell at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: old-fashioned pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Beat eggs until lemon colored (about 3 minutes).
Beating well after each ingredient, add these to egg in order given: sugar, vanilla, clear syrup and cane syrup.
Next add flour mixture alternately with orange juice, then add orange peel and pecans.
Pour in uncooked pie crust and cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 280°.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes until nice and fluffy.
Similar to custard or pudding.

title: surprise meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar, mint and vanilla extracts.
Slowly add sugar and beat well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 275° for about 30 minutes.
When done, let cookies cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over sugar.
Let stand until warm.
Add yeast dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add beaten egg and 2 cups flour. Add melted shortening.
Let stand, covered, for 30 minutes, then add remaining 1 1/2 cups flour and salt.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, roll out on floured board.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes.

title: lemon velvet
directions: Place half each of yogurt, orange juice concentrate, skim milk and vanilla in container of an electric blender.
Add enough ice cubes to measure 3 1/2 cups; blend until smooth.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 7 cups.

title: try-this-dip
directions: May add shrimp or ham or just use your imagination.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar
and butter.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix in flour and milk alternately.
Roll out on floured board, adding flour until dough is firm enough to cut.	Thin dough will make crispy cookies.
Thick
dough
makes softer cookies.
Bake at 325° about 7 minutes.

title: interstate 45 minute cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 egg, crem cheese, powdered sugar and brown sugar.
Spread over mixture.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
30 pieces.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix food coloring and cocoa.
Add to sugar and butter mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla with flour and salt.
In a small bowl mix vinegar and soda together; fold into other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: yellow cake
directions: Blend eggs, butter and water into cake mix.
Beat on low speed for 30 seconds.
Then beat on high speed for 4 minutes or until the mixture is smooth.
Grease pan, add mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coffee squares
directions: Mix brown sugar and eggs together.
Add oil, then coffee and vanilla.
Add salt and soda to flour; sift into the mixture.
Mix well.
Place in a large cookie sheet.
Don't forget to grease and flour bottom of pan.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Maybe less time; depends on how well oven heats.)

title: chewy noels
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square pan over low heat; remove from heat.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, soda and nuts and mix well. Stir in vanilla and pour into pan over melted butter.
Do not stir mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn out of pan; cut into bars.
Dust with confectioners sugar; cool.
Yields 3 dozen bars.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs by hand until frothy, about 3 minutes. Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini; mix well with spatula.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Spray 2 loaf pans with a cooking spray and lightly flour.
Divide batter evenly between pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool in pans, then gently turn out onto serving dish.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat egg and egg yolks until light and fluffy.	Beat in water and salt.
Knead with hands 2 cups flour.
Makes into a ball form.

title: herbed black-eyed peas
directions: Cover peas with water.
Soak overnight; drain.
(Frozen or fresh peas can be substituted.)
Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add peas and enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in sugar and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, until peas are soft.

title: mock apple cake
directions: Boil water, sugar and cream of tartar for 2 minutes.
Drop in 20 Ritz crackers (do not stir) and boil for 1 minute longer. Remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Let cool.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's pizza
directions: Mix together flour, salt and sugar. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add yeast mixture and oil to flour, stirring to make soft dough, but not sticky. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; add more flour if dough is sticky. Knead about 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic. Put dough in lightly oiled bowl; brush with oil. Cover with towel. Put in a warm place. Let rise until doubled in size (about 2 hours). Remove dough from bowl; punch it down on a lightly floured surface. Divide into 2 equal balls. Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Taking 1 ball at a time, roll out in a circle about 14-inches in diameter. The dough should be thinner at the center
than at the edge. Place each circle on a pizza pan or baking sheet. Pinch the edge of dough up to form a rim. Prick lightly all over with a fork. Fill with favorite filling. (Yields 2 pizzas.)

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix bananas and margarine. Add flour and soda. Add other ingredients. Add nuts last. Mix all together with a large wooden spoon. Spray muffin tins with Pam or Baker's Secret spray. Bake in 300° oven until done. These are great for a breakfast muffin. Keep extras in refrigerator and warm in microwave. Makes 20 to 24 regular-size muffins.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve puddings and jello in boiling water.
Let stand until syrupy.
Add pineapple and oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 pan and chill.

title: pork tenderloin with sauce
directions: Trim excess fat from pork.
Cut 3 cloves garlic into slivers. Moisten with water and roll in the crushed rosemary.
Cut small slashes on both sides of pork; insert garlic into holes.
Sprinkle meat generously with pepper and seasoned salt.
Wrap tightly in foil and refrigerate.

title: chicken stew
directions: In large pot, pour milk over cooked noodles, add chicken, broth and margarine.
Warm, stir often to prevent sticking.
Add seasonings.
Crumble saltines and add to thicken.
Freezes okay.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; roll in balls.
Place on wax paper.
Melt wax and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpicks.
Place on wax paper.

title: party potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes; drain.
Beat cheese and sour cream to blend.
Gradually add hot potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Add seasoning.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole. Brush with butter and brown in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: heath cookies
directions: Break apart and put graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Boil sugar and butter together for 2 minutes.
Chop amount of almonds or pecans desired.
Spread liquid over the graham crackers. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and cool on wax paper.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute in large boiler the onions, pepper, butter and salt to taste and broccoli about 5 minutes.
Add canned milk, whole milk and salmon (stir continuously).
Bring to boil; cut off immediately.
Serve hot.
(If you like oyster stew, you will love this.)
You may enlarge ingredients to fit the number you serve. This will serve approximately 4.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes (peeled or not) for mashing.
Salt if desired. Mash potatoes and add cream cheese and sour cream (add no-fat variety if you like).
Dot with butter.
Put into casserole and cover with foil.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Warm in slow oven.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.
If reheated in microwave, cover casserole with Saran Wrap and warm on Medium power.

title: ground beef or deer salami
directions: Mix spices in water and stir.
Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Form all into a large roll about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in foil, shiny side out.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Poke holes in bottom of package.
Place on broiler rack with pan of water underneath.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes; unwrap and cool. Wrap in plastic for storage.

title: baked salmon supreme
directions: Cook asparagus; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine eggs, milk, herbs, salt and onion.
Fold in flaked salmon.
Reserve 6 asparagus spears; place rest in pastry shell.
Pour in salmon mixture.
Top with 6 asparagus spears left.
Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: toasted almond spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Spread into a pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Garnish with additional almonds.
Serve with crackers or bread cutouts.

title: california chicken dish
directions: Simmer or pressure
chicken
until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Sprinkle onion
soup
mix
over
bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle rice over onion
soup mix.
Lay chicken on top of rice. Dilute soup with
broth and place over chicken.
Dot with butter.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix together and beat until thick milk, pudding and Dream Whip mix.
Pour pie filling into baked crust.
Spread pudding mixture over cherries.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: thelma's dinner buns
directions: Combine water and yeast in large bowl.
Add salt, sugar, honey and one melted stick of margarine.
Sift and stir in enough flour to make a very stiff dough.
Let rise in a greased covered dish until double in bulk.
Then work down on a well floured surface. Knead well and shape into buns.
Place into 2 large bread pans, greased with margarine, and top buns with remaining margarine. Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: dave's margaritas
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and fill blender with crushed ice.
Blend until desired consistency. Pour into margarita glasses that have been coated around the rim with lemon/lime juice and dipped in salt.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook in frying pan, the celery and onions in water and liquid from mushrooms.
Add the cooked meat (leftover roast is best), the mushrooms, and bouillon cubes.
Simmer 15 minutes and serve over cooked rice.
Add 1 can of noodles on top.

title: spicy sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Pour off drippings. Reduce heat. Add pepper, onion, tomatoes, macaroni and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts. Yields 2 servings.

title: backyard potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet; drain. Add onions; cook until tender.
Add cooked potatoes, hard-cooked eggs and parsley.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add combined bacon, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Serve hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie dough in a cookie pan as per directions for 10 minutes; allow to cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice until smooth; spread over cool cookie cake.
Arrange fruits in decorative pattern.
Chill and serve.

title: hawaiian beets
directions: Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and pineapple with its juice in heavy saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add beets, margarine and lemon juice coating beets with pineapple mixture.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Heat oven to 400.
Drain oysters well.
Combine crumbs, pepper, and butter.
Sprinkle 1/3 of mixture in well greased baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 of oysters, and another layer of crumbs and the rest of oysters.
Pour milk over all - put balance of crumbs over all.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: angel cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased pan at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be baked in muffin pan or regular pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits; roll and dust each piece with a sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Layer biscuits in a Bundt pan or in an angel food cake pan.
Melt butter, sugar and cinnamon on stove until it bubbles; pour mixture over layered biscuit quarters.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Glaze with a milk-powdered sugar mixture.

title: turkey carcass soup
directions: Bring carcass to a boil in large pot; then simmer for 2 hours. Take
carcass
out
of
water and remove meat.
Return meat to pot
and
add
remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour. Yields 5 quarts.

title: crab dunk
directions: Mash cream cheese and add all other; adjust to taste.
Serve with crackers or veggie dippers.
Nice for the holidays.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first 2 ingredients; gradually add both sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chips and vanilla.
Spread in a 9-inch square buttered pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares. Makes 16.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Melt butter; add all other ingredients.
Use cooking no-stick spray on cookie sheet and drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: emma's cornbread
directions: Put in hot pan.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: chex after-school mix(microwave)
directions: Place cereals in
large
bowl;
set
aside.
In 1 quart microwavesafe bowl,
combine
chocolate
pieces, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on
High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after one minute; stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereals, stirring until
all
pieces are evenly coated.
Place cereal mixture and sugar in large paper or plastic bag;
shake until all pieces are
well
coated.
Spread
on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: thailand rice dish
directions: Fry meat lightly in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Add mushrooms, rice, onion and soy sauce.
Fry over low heat 10 minutes.
Add egg.
Cook and stir 5 more minutes.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into small pieces and mix all ingredients in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: apple jelly
directions: Mix juice, pectin, butter and water in a large pot. Stir constantly over high heat, bringing it to a full boil. Add sugar all at once, stirring to dissolve. Bring to a full boil again and let boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Pour into jars, seal and turn upside down for 5 minutes. Turn right side up and let cool.

title: primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Heat oil; saute onion and garlic for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: beau monde and dill weed dip
directions: Mix well and serve with raw cauliflower, broccoli, carrot sticks or as a dip with chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water; beat.
Stir in dry ingredients and then add the nuts and raisins. Bake in greased bread pans at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
They are done when a wooden toothpick tests clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples.
Turn into ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Dot with butter.
Unfold pastry over fruit; fold edges under just inside edge of pan.
Bake 1 hour or until juice begins to bubble through slits in crust. Best served warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: easy casserole
directions: Add soy sauce, lemon juice and onion soup mix to beef, salt and pepper.
Layer in buttered casserole with potatoes.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Top may be sprinkled with some grated cheese about 5 minutes before removing from oven.

title: chicken squares
directions: Grind cooked macaroni in grinder or food processor.
Mix together all ingredients except cream and paprika.
Whip the cream and fold in.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Set in another pan containing hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Cut in squares.
Serve with sauce.

title: chicago deep dish pizza
directions: Grease a 14 x 2-inch pizza pan.
On flour-dusted board, roll dough to a 16-inch circle.
Press into bottom and 1 1/2 inches up the sides of pan.
Sprinkle 3 cups cheese on crust.
Crumble sausage over cheese.

title: raspberry delight cranberry sauce(this is great for thanksgiving.)
directions: Cook cranberries per package directions using the juice, syrup, fresh cranberries and orange zest.
Stir in pecans, if desired, at end.

title: crunchy nut cookie(good for dunking)
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Shape 1 level tablespoon dough into balls; place on ungreased pan.
Flatten with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet until no longer pink, breaking up with fork as you cook.
(about 8-10 minutes)
Drain off fat and spoon sausage into large bowl and cool completely.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water.
Mix with a fork until blended.
Roll into 1 inch balls and place on a baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes, or until puffed and brown.
Remove from baking sheet and cool completely.
Makes 120 puffs.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put margarine, oil and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Mix in sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Put in ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut into oleo. Add buttermilk. Stir to mix well. Knead 1/2 minute. Roll or pat out to 1/2 inch thick. Cut biscuits. Place on greased cookie sheet. Prick tops with fork. Brush with buttermilk. Bake at 450 degree for 10-12 minutes.

title: easy potato casserole(i'm not on my diet tonight casserole)
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 baking dish with cooking spray.
Place the Tater Tots in the pan in a single layer.
Add milk.
Sprinkle on garlic and onion salt.
Slice butter into pats and place on top. Then slice the Velveeta and place on top of that.
Bake for 45 minutes at 425°.
Remove and stir.
Place back in the oven for an additional 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: cream cheese rugelach
directions: In a food processor, combine butter, cream cheese and superfine sugar.
Process until well blended.
Add cake flour and salt.
Process until dough forms a ball around the blades.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate 1 hour until firm.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine walnuts, chocolate, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.

title: greek butter cookies
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter until light.
Gradually add 2 cups 4x sugar, beating at low speed. Beat in egg yolks and brandy.
Stir in flour with salt and baking powder; gradually beat into mixture.
Blend in vanilla; knead dough until smooth.
Using about 1 tablespoon dough, roll into ball shapes.
Place cookies on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 20 minutes.
Cookies will be pale golden.
Roll in remaining 1 cup 4x sugar while warm.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: date pudding
directions: Boil brown sugar and water for a few minutes.
Mix and pour other ingredients into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the hot syrup mixture on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yum-yum.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine
sugar, water, cornstarch and corn syrup.
Cook until clear.
Add
salt,	jello
and
a few drops of red food coloring. Cool;
add	strawberries.
Fill baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.
If frozen berries are used, drain the juice and use
instead
of water.
Graham cracker crust may be used if desired.

title: aunt fannie's raisin pie
directions: Place raisins in pot and cover with water. In a medium bowl, place egg yolks and sugar and cream together. Add flavorings, cinnamon, nutmeg and mix. Bring raisin mixture to low boil and gently add in creamed mixture. Mix cornstarch with a little of raisin liquid and gently stir into raisin mixture. Heat until thickened to medium consistency. Pour into prepared pie crust. Top with remaining crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Put rinsed asparagus no more than 2 layers deep in a buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: After chicken is cleaned and dressed, cut it into serving portions.
Flour lightly and saute in butter along with chopped onions.
When chicken is nicely browned, add okra, tomatoes, parsley and water.
Cook very slowly until chicken is tender and okra well cooked, 2 1/2 hours.
Add water as required during the slow cooking process.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
If thin soup is preferred, increase the amount of water.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, chili powder, cumin and red pepper in large bowl; mix until well blended.
Stir in salsa. Spread onto 10-inch serving platter lined with lettuce.
Top with cheeses, tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Serve with chips.

title: lemon pie
directions: Squeeze lemons and stir in milk.
Pour into pie crust. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top or you may use vanilla wafers on top, if desired.
Refrigerate for firmness.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Stir flours, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, beat egg, then add milk and margarine.
Combine with flour mixture. Stir until blended, but still lumpy. Spray griddle.

title: korean beef bagolgie
directions: Mix ingredients all together and marinate for 24 hours.
Broil until cooked (it doesn't take very long). Serve with rice.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef, onion, and garlic in butter.
Add seasoning, olives, and tomato sauce.
In a 2 quart casserole dish, alternate layers of corn chips, meat sauce, and 1 1/2 c. cheese.
Top with remaining 1/2 c. cheese.
Add 2/3 c. water.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or longer if cheese has not melted.
Serve with salad.

title: orange chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into mixture of eggs and orange juice, then into mixture of bread crumbs, salt, paprika and shredded peel. Melt butter in large shallow baking pan in 400° oven.
Remove pan from oven.
Turn chicken in butter to coat.
Arrange skin side down (don't crowd).
Bake 30 minutes.
Yumm!
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce until smooth.
Spread in bottom of oblong casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with lettuce, onion, cheese and tomatoes.

title: miss piggy's precious pink punch
directions: Combine chilled ingredients in a punch bowl or large pitcher. Garnish with lemon slices and mint.
Serves 14.

title: steak diane
directions: Sprinkle steaks with lemon pepper seasoning.
Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until margarine melts.
Add steaks and cook 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness. Transfer to a platter.
Keep warm.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard to skillet.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over steaks.
Garnish with lemon twists, as desired.
Makes 6 servings (179 calories; 8.2 grams of fat).

title: nissley's original layer casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 to 2 hours.

title: con queso dip
directions: Brown meat in onion and garlic.
Drain.
Melt Velveeta in microwave-safe bowl in microwave with salsa approximately 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir to blend.
Add ground meat.
Cover and heat on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir and cover again and heat again 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir and cover again and heat again 1 to 2 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: all at once spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in saucepan or skillet.
Add onion; cook until soft. Crumble in the beef.
Stir and fry until meat loses red color. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour in tomato sauce and water; bring to boil.
Break spaghetti; sprinkle in a little at a time, stirring into sauce and keeping it separated.
Cover tightly. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir toward end of cooking time.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: persimmon bar cookies
directions: Combine salt, flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Beat eggs and add sugar gradually.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Spread in a greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet or two 9 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cool, frost with Orange Cream Cheese Frosting and cut into bars.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar and cream.
Bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes. Take off stove and add butter, peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered dish and refrigerate.

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in Wesson oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Enough sauce for basting and serving 2 chickens.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and margarine until tender.
Add soup, chicken (chopped) and seasoning.
Boil noodles in salt water or chicken broth; drain.
Add noodles to mixture.
Pour mixture into greased pan; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: favorite berry cobbler
directions: Sweeten berries or
fruit
to
taste and place in a 7 x 11-inch baking
pan.
Preheat
oven
to
Combine
brown sugar and oil
in
a medium bowl; stir in flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix
well
with
a
fork
or pastry blender. Spoon mixture evenly over fruit.	Dot with butter or margarine cut into small pieces.
Arrange walnut or pecan pieces on top. Bake	for 40 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.
Top with whipped topping. Serves 6 to 8.

title: never-fail rolled biscuits(these light biscuits separate into layers)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C).
Combine Quick Mix and milk or water in a medium bowl.
Blend.
Let dough stand 5 minutes. On a lightly floured board, knead dough about 15 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a floured biscuit cutter. Place about 2 inches apart on unbuttered baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 12 large biscuits.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat. Add cheese; stir until dissolved.
Add soup mixture to noodle mixture.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Melt butter and Velveeta in milk.
Place hash browns in greased baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecanettes
directions: Cream butter and soften cream cheese.
Add flour; mix well. Divide into 24 balls and press into miniature muffin tins.

title: crumb pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside for top.
Mix remaining 3 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Add dry mixture on top and bake.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Place in 2-pound loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix oil and flour to make a roux.
Add celery, onions and garlic and cook until onions are clear.
Add broth, clams and potatoes.
Cook until all vegetables are tender.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts, cherries, chocolate and coconut.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Boil potatoes in water with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Saute bacon; add onions and saute until tender; drain grease.
Mix in 3 tablespoons flour and add the milk.
Add potatoes and clams, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: crock-pot casserole(lo-cal)
directions: Cut wieners into bite-size pieces.
Place wieners, jelly and mustard into crock-pot.
Slow cook 4 to 6 hours.
Serve as finger foods (with toothpicks) or serve as main dish over bed of rice or noodles.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled for large parties or family dinners.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Stir all
together except eggplant.
Drain eggplant and add to mixture.
Put in greased glass dish and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: susan's baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter, salt and pepper until smooth. Remove from stove.
Stir in flour and return to heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer mixture 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Velveeta cheese and the macaroni.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes, or until cheese is golden brown.

title: sorghum molasses cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add to creamed mixture.
Add molasses.
Combine flour, salt, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Batter will be thick.
Add 1 cup hot water. Do not add extra flour.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at moderate heat for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add garlic, parsley flakes, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Cook noodles in salted water.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and cheese.
Grease a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread half the noodles on bottom of pan; cover with half the cottage cheese mixture and cover this with half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat these layers.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
This recipe can be prepared, divided and put in smaller pans to freeze for later use.

title: whipper snappers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Place teaspoon of mixture into powdered sugar and roll into ball.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into florets.
Place in a bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Cover and let stand 2 hours.
After 2 hours, rinse cauliflower and dry well.

title: german potato bake
directions: In a large saucepan combine potatoes, 1/4 pound process cheese spread and margarine;
stir
over low heat until cheese is melted. Add
tablespoons
bacon,
2 tablespoons onions, salad dressing, sour
cream,
pimento
and
pepper;
mix well. Spoon into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese spread, bacon and
onions.	Sprinkle
with	paprika.
Bake	at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: boiled drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients
with
a
spoon (dry ingredients first) and bake in greased and floured tube pan.
(I used a Bundt pan and like it much
better,
the
cake
took less time to cook.) Bake at 300° for
1 hour in regular tube pan (mine required an additional 20 minutes).
Stick
a
wooden toothpick in cake to test it.
If toothpick
is clean, it's done.
Don't overcook. You want it to be good and moist.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, water, butter, shortening, sugar and about half of dry cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, the oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook until transparent.
Discard oil.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons paprika on chicken to coat.
Sprinkle flour on top and stir.
Add chicken stock, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly until chicken is very tender.
Add sour cream last 5 minutes only to heat.
Do not boil.
Gravy will be thin.
Serve with boiled potatoes or parslied noodles.

title: pecan turtle bars
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and butter.
Mix at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl often, 2 to 3 minutes, until particles are fine.
Pat firmly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place pecan halves evenly over unbaked crust.

title: opulent chicken
directions: Melt butter in saute pan and brown chicken breasts on both sides.
Remove chicken and put in square baking dish.
Put mushrooms and artichoke hearts in saute pan and cook for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms and artichokes.
Add chicken broth, sherry and tarragon.
Stir and let bubble until it thickens a bit.
Pour over chicken and cook for 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add onion and frozen broccoli to melted margarine.
Heat slowly until broccoli is thawed and then drain.
Cook rice according to directions.
Mix rice, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Place in casserole dish alternately with broccoli, beginning and ending with rice mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in large salad bowl in the order listed, first five items.
Then cover completely with Hellmann's.
Then sprinkle Hellmann's with the cheese.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Skin cooled chicken and roll in flour.
Fry in butter in electric skillet until light brown (low heat); remove chicken and set aside.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together; form into cakes.
Fry in hot grease in frying pan.
Drain on paper towels, then remove to serving plate.

title: sharon's scalloped chicken
directions: Mix
together
all
ingredients except for the soup and cheese.
Put
in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Before baking, spread cream
of
mushroom
soup
on
top.
Bake
at 300° for 1 hour. Sprinkle
with grated cheese, then bake 10 minutes more.
This can be made the day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: queen of muffins
directions: Combine and divide into muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: fruit ball
directions: Chop fruit cocktail fine.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and juice.
Add fruit and mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in almonds.
Chill.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: scalloped corn souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat corn and milk; gradually stir in egg.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs over top.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend eggs into margarine mixture, one at a time.
In a separate bowl, sift dry ingredients together and mix with vanilla.
Add egg mixture.
Fold in apples.
Turn mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: roast beef casserole
directions: Cook celery, onions and pepper in 2 tablespoons oil or margarine until clear.
Add beef cubes.
Cook several minutes. Stir in soups, water, salt, soy sauce and Tabasco.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve over rice or creamed potatoes.

title: skillet corn
directions: Heat an 8-inch ovenproof iron skillet in a 425° oven.
After 20 minutes, pour in the oil.
Meanwhile, stir together all the other ingredients.
Scrape into the heated pan.
Do not stir; pat into an even layer.

title: aunt tessie's hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and thick.
Slowly add sugar and beat with a spoon for 5 minutes.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Fold into eggs and sugar.
Mix all at one time, quickly.
Melt butter in hot milk and add all at once.
The folding in of flour and milk should take 60 seconds!
Bake in 7-inch square pan in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Then add all ingredients together. Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish or 2 round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick chicken and rice casserole
directions: First, boil the chicken breasts until cooked.
Then cut into small chunks.
Boil rice as directed.
While cooking rice, cook stuffing as directed on stove top.
Mix chicken with cream of chicken soup, then add rice.
Stir well.
Spray casserole pan with Pam cooking spray.
Spread mixture in the casserole pan.
Spread stuffing over chicken and rice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until stuffing browns.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir cheese soup and milk together until smooth.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions and soup.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour, then uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: divinity candy
directions: Blend sugar and syrup with water in saucepan.
Cook until a hard boil.
Pour over egg whites gradually, beating constantly. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape when dropped from spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or pour into well buttered pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: pizza dough
directions: Blend together the bread flour, dry yeast and salt.
Add warm water and mix 10 minutes.
Let rise 1 hour.
Divide dough into 2 pieces and ball up.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Roll out piece to size of pan and put on pan.
Put on desired toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: howard's cheesy halibut
directions: Cut fish into pieces approximately 2 x 2-inch. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Blend garlic with the oil. Place fish in oil for about a minute. Mix the Cheddar and bread crumbs together. Remove fish pieces from oil; drain off a bit and then roll in the crumb/Cheddar mixture. Place on baking pan and bake in hot oven (450°) for 12 minutes or until browned.

title: "a-1" beef tenderloins
directions: Cut beef cubes into bite-size pieces (partially freeze beef cubes for easier cutting).
Saute cubes in frypan with butter or margarine, until tender.
Add steak sauce and teriyaki sauce to beef.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add pepper, mushrooms (cut in thin strips) and onion to beef.
Simmer an additional 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve over rice or noodles, or serve plain as a main dish.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice and condensed milk well.
Add blackberries; stir until mixed.
Pour into either 2 baked pie shells or 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: swiss sandwich puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and spread onto 32 toasted slices of rye bread.
Top each with 1/4 slice Swiss cheese.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Can omit oats or any of last 6 ingredients.
Mix all in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 325 F till lightly browned, 10-12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil and remove.
Brown onion in same pan and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes, then pour over chicken in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pear honey
directions: Use firm unripe pears.
Peel and core; using coarse blade, grind pears.
Combine pears and sugar; cook mixture until pears are clear, about 35 minutes.
Add the undrained pineapple, then cook a few minutes longer.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Mix sugar and butter together until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hamburger rice hot dish
directions: Pour hot water over rice.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, 1 cup confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Mix puddings and cold milk together and let stand for a few minutes.
Pour over 2nd layer.
Top with Cool Whip, drizzle with chocolate syrup and sprinkle with nuts.

title: peach crunch
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Put in Pyrex dish.
Mix all the other ingredients.
Cover peaches with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut the crust from the bread slices and cut each slice into 5 fingers or strips.
Place the bread fingers over the fruit.
In a bowl, mix the sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over the fruit and bread.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Cream first three ingredients and one tablespoon of water. Stir in flour and nuts, mix well.
Shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 15 - 20 minutes. Cool on a rack.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: playdo bars
directions: In a large pan, melt oil, margarine, marshmallows and caramels.
Stir in half the popcorn and remove from heat.
Add candy, nuts and remaining corn.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Store in covered container.

title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Pare cucumber and quarter lengthwise. Remove seeds. Cut in small cubes. Seed green peppers and cut into cubes. Dice celery. Peel onion and chop coarsely. Cube hard-cooked eggs and toasts. Place cucumber, green pepper, celery, onion, eggs and toast cubes in individual serving dishes. Reserve for serving. Puree tomatoes. Combine with tomato juice, consomme, vinegar and salt in blender or food processor and blend well. Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate for several hours. Serve in the reserved individual bowl with the rest of the prepared ingredients. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in a small amount of oil.
Add chopped broccoli and bouillon. Cover and simmer a few minutes. Add pimentos and milk. Simmer awhile longer. Take 1 cup cold milk and mix with flour.
Add to soup.
Cook until thickened.
Reheat slowly, if needed.

title: basque soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grandmother lowman's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix.
Use half the flour to dust the raisins, currants, citron, dates, figs and nuts.
Mix spices with remaining flour.
Add grape juice to creamed mixture and add remaining dry ingredients.
Grease and line with brown paper a tube or loaf pan(s).
Fill the pan(s) half full with mixture.
Bake in a slow 225° oven for 3 hours or until done.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle with 1/2 stick melted oleo and 2 cups crushed corn flakes before baking.

title: microwave chocolate cake
directions: Grease round micro-proof baking dish, 7 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch or 8 x 1 1/2-inches; line bottom with plastic wrap.
In small microwave-proof bowl, combine cocoa and 1/3 cup water; microwave on High 40 to 50 seconds or until slightly thickened.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oil, remaining 1/3 cup hot water, egg, vanilla and chocolate mixture; beat until batter is smooth and well blended.
Pour batter into pan.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes without turning until cake begins to pull away from sides.
Let stand 5 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Peel off plastic wrap; cool.
Frost.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and add alternately with the sour milk and mashed bananas.
Add vanilla (nuts if desired).
I prefer walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured layer cake pans or loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven or low about 1 hour.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Butter 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place blackberries in bottom of dish.
Combine in bowl the Bisquick mix, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over berries and place pieces over sprinkled mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: In bowl combine melted butter, onion, salt, cottage cheese, broccoli and beaten eggs.
Blend and stir in the muffin mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°. Cut into serving squares.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake as directed, adding pudding mix last.
Bake in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
(Will be thin.)

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar (on No. 8 of the mixer) until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Reduce mixer speed (to No. 2).
Add flour and cream alternately.
(Beat after each addition.)
Spoon into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Put into cold oven to bake at 350° for 1 hour and reduce heat to 325° to continue baking until done (about 20 minutes).

title: pumpkin bread(4 cans)
directions: Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) cans (coffee cans).
Fill about half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make at least 1 day before using, add nuts and raisins if desired.
This can be cooked in bread loaf pans.
(I add 1 cup raisins and 1 cup nuts.)

title: green beans with personality
directions: Put oil in a frying pan.
Add green beans and tarragon.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, salt and pepper. Continue cooking another 5 minutes, until sugar is dissolved and green beans are tender yet still crisp.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix with mixer or blender.

title: date and nut loaf bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and spices.
Add to eggs and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until loaf leaves the sides of pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese in large bowl.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Add crumbs to melted oleo and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: dad's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all ingredients in Dutch oven and simmer at least an hour.
Serve with crackers, cornbread, Fritos and cheese.

title: barbecue pork and bean bake
directions: Place baked beans in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spread lightly with mustard, sprinkle with sugar and spread with catsup.
Arrange over beans.
With toothpick, attach slice of onion and lemon to each piece.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for about 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.

title: tenderloin
directions: Sprinkle with seasoning.
Place in bag.
Pour in wine, tie and refrigerate overnight. Cut 6 1/2 inch slits in top of bag. Place on roasting pan and bake at 325 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes or 140 degrees on meat thermometer.

title: raisin-cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water, stirring until dissolved.
Mix sugar, margarine and egg.
Add yeast liquid.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place sweet potatoes in a greased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
In a saucepan, combine margarine, brown sugar, honey, cinnamon and salt.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Evenly spoon over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.
May also top with nuts, if desired, before baking.

title: dumplings
directions: Stir flour, Crisco, salt and egg.
Add milk.
Roll out on waxed paper covered with flour.
Roll as thin as you can.
Freeze on wax paper in layers.
Cook until tender in hot boiling chicken broth.
For many dumplings, you will need to make more than one recipe.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine all salad ingredients.
Ingredients and proportions may be varied to taste.
Marinated artichoke hearts are an excellent addition.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Add a little flour to the drippings.
Stir well and cook until a light brown, then pour in some hot water, stirring steadily until it thickens.

title: rocky road clusters
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in 2-quart glass bowl.
Stir in milk and butter.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave for 4 minutes on High or until mixture comes to full boil.
Stir well.
Continue cooking 1 minute on High.
Remove from oven and stir in vanilla.
Add oats and walnuts; stir.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Add raisins and marshmallows.
Stir until swirled.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Refrigerate to set.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: delicious mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix the ingredients on low speed of a mixer.
Put it on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake as directed on the box.

title: braised chicken and string beans
directions: Place a kettle on the stove
and
let
water
come to a boil. Snap green beans;
wash
in
cool water and drain.	Add to the boiling water and
precook beans for 20 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Wash chicken
pieces in cool water;
drain and pat dry to remove water.

title: un-fried french fries(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice each oval into lengthwise matchsticks.
Coat baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.
Combine egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add potatoes and mix to coat.
Return to baking sheet, leaving a little space between.
Cook on bottom shelf.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until crispy, turning often.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli (not completely).
Mix next 6 ingredients together.
Lay broccoli in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour mixture over broccoli.
Cover top with crumbled crackers and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir flour and salt together; blend in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
(Cookies do not spread.)
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not let brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grate zucchini squash and place in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Place cheese slices over zucchini, and dot with butter.
Spread rice evenly over cheese; then cover with onion, mushrooms and bacon bits.
Mix water with soup and pour over this layer.
Sprinkle generously with All-Season seasoning, then top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cook on bottom rack of oven.

title: potato hamburger casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, hamburger and onion in baking dish.
Pour soups over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
When 3/4 done, stir soups in the potatoes.

title: best ever meat balls
directions: Form into balls about the size of a silver dollar.
Simmer in the Sauce for about 30 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crust.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Freeze and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: raspberry cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and jello.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
After mixing, roll into balls and press flat with a glass.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: combination pizza
directions: Spread biscuit dough onto greased pizza pan.
Spread half a jar of pizza sauce over dough.
Combine cheeses and spread over sauce.
Layer pepperoni, onion and olives.
Preheat oven to 400° and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is light brown.

title: cheese casserole bread
directions: Preparation Time:
25 minutes. Rising Time:
2 hours. Baking Time:
20 to 25 minutes. Oven Temperature:

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Fry meat, onion and bell pepper together until meat browns and the onion and pepper are tender.
Mix these together and add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Chop a large jalapeno pepper and add to mix if you like hot and spicy taste.)
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and nuts.
Pat into bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes; cool.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Make crumbs of top 3 ingredients.
Put in 11 x 5 x 1 in. pan. Bake for 10 min.
Mix the rest together, cook and pour on crust. Bake for 25 min.
Beat 6 egg whites.
While beating, add 1-2 Tbsp. sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla, beat till stiff.
Pour on cake and bake till golden.
Very good!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour 3 times with baking soda and salt.
Cream the butter and both sugars until soft and well blended (but not fluffy).
Add egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in flour.
Knead in bowl until dough is smooth.
Divide into 2 parts and roll each part into a roll.
Cut into 1-inch pieces. Place pieces 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Press with the tip of a fork to form crisscrosses on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix in container (1 gallon) with water enough to make 1 gallon.
Ready to serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: meat marinade of '87
directions: Slice meat into 1/2-inch strips and marinate in mixture for several hours, turning frequently.
Can be cooked in wok with Chinese vegetables or a mixture of soft kidney beans, snow peas, sliced onions, celery, artichoke hearts and carrots.
Do not overcook vegetables.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixer bowl; beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling on wire racks. Frost with Coconut Cream Frosting.

title: cheese log supreme
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Chop beef and onions. Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Form into log and roll in nuts. Wrap in foil and refrigerate or freeze.
Serve with crackers.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops; pour off fat. Season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until rice is done. Stir often.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter. Add other ingredients, mixing well. Roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 325 to 350 degrees about 10 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Thaw okra in microwave.
In a medium saucepan, add all vegetables.
Add salt, pepper and Cajun seasoning to your family's taste.
Go easy on the salt because most tomatoes already have salt.
Cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate lover's cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup chocolate chips; mix well.
Fold in 1/2 cup chips.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 12 cup tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
For Teflon lined pan, reduce heat to 325°.

title: baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Saute chicken in butter. Combine the other ingredients.
Arrange chicken in baking dish and pour the mixture over it.
Bake one hour.
Serve over 1 cup white or wild rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: kielbasa chilli
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain excess fat.
In ground beef, brown 1/2 bell pepper and 1/2 onion.
In crock-pot, add beef mixture, tomato paste, tomatoes and rest of onions and bell peppers.
Cut sausage into 1/2 inch thick slices; add to beef mixture.
Cut jalapeno pepper into small pieces and add.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until sausage is tender.
Garnish with cheese and serve crackers.
Enjoy.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together; refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone fryer.
Save broth and cook spaghetti until tender.
Add to broth, chicken and all soups and tomato sauce.
Do not dilute but may rinse out cans with a little water.
Spaghetti will freeze.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion and drain grease. Add tomatoes, Ro-Tel and mushrooms. Simmer for 30 minutes on low heat. Cook and drain spaghetti noodles (do not rinse). Add margarine and garlic salt. Stir gently until margarine melts.

title: best seven minute frosting
directions: Bring Karo to boil.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy. Slowly add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Add hot syrup and beat well. Add vanilla.

title: "krispy" chicken
directions: Use a large baggie to crush cereal.
Add next 4 ingredients into bag and shake.
Dip chicken into margarine and toss in bag of cereal.
Shake to coat each piece of chicken.
Bake at 400° on greased pan for about 20 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Work shortening with spoon until creamy.
Add sugar gradually, while continuing to work until light.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, blending well with spoon with each addition. Add nuts and enough of 1/2 cup flour to make a soft, easily handled dough.
Chill 1 hour or longer.
Roll dough on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness; cut out with floured doughnut cutter.
Form trimmings into a ball; roll and cut as before.

title: mom's new years cookies
directions: Mix together and let raise in warm place.
(I set bowl in oven with the light on.)
Stir down and let raise 1/2 hour and bake in deep fat.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix Bisquick, water and refried beans.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Layer other ingredients as listed.
Top with sour cream, green onions and tomatoes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Ready to serve.

title: milky wonder cake
directions: Melt bars and one-half cup butter over very low heat.
Beat remaining one-half cup butter and sugar in a medium size bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched with fingertips.
Top will be quite dark.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
May be frosted if you wish.

title: honey chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Let stand for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Foil cookie sheet.
Place wings on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with garlic powder. Baste chicken with mixture.
Cook for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: turtle fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with foil; butter foil.
In large pan, combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and chocolate chips; blend until smooth.
Stir in cashews, caramels and vanilla.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut unpeeled cucumbers and slice onions.
Combine onions, salt and cucumbers.
Soak in water for 3 hours.
Rinse with cold water. Drain off.
Combine last ingredients. Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add pickles and onions.
Heat to boiling. Place in sterile cans and seal at once. Yields 5 pints.

title: salted pecans
directions: Cut butter in small chunks and scatter over top of nuts. Place nuts in 450° oven.
Stir often until butter is melted. Remove and stir in salt to taste; let cool.

title: lemon bars
directions: Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool completely and serve.

title: della lou's pizza
directions: Mix water, yeast, oil and flour to make crust.
Let rise until dough is doubled.
Mix sauce and paste together.
Roll dough out after punching down.
Place on pizza pan.
Spread sauce on top. Top with your favorite pizza toppings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kentucky spiced tea
directions: Put sugar, cold water and spices (tied in a bag) in an enamel or stainless pan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 10 minutes.
Put in tea leaves (tied in a bag).
Add 12 cups hot water and juices. Steep 5 minutes.
Strain if desired.

title: old fashioned shortbread cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugars.
Add egg yolks, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Microwave on High 19 minutes.
Every 5 minutes, stir and turn bowl.
Beat the egg whites stiff.
Pour sugar mixture into egg whites and beat until stiff and mixture loses glossy color (about 12 to 15 minutes on high speed).
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup, melted margarine and butter flavoring.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of filling comes out clean.
Cool.

title: tomatoes stuffed with chicken salad
directions: Cut caps off tomatoes and reserve.
Scoop out deep hollow. Turn upside down to drain 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Stuff tomatoes with mixture and press caps on top.
Refrigerate.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: spinach pie (spanakopita)
directions: Pour 1/2 cup butter in saucepan.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Combine Feta cheese, cottage cheese, drained spinach and farina in large bowl.
Stir in onion mixture.
Add eggs gradually, stirring constantly.
Season and set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in eggs, then broccoli. Place in casserole dish and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: holiday pecan pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 25 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Leave sausage and grated cheese at room temperature, approximately 30 minutes.
Mix together with paprika.
Add Bisquick and mix well.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 100 balls!

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook spiral noodles; drain.
Let cool.
Fry bacon until crisp. When cool, break apart.
Drain tuna fish; let peas thaw, do not cook.
Mix remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix liquid ingredients, then sift and add dry ingredients. Mix well again.
Refrigerate dough for several hours.
Roll in small balls.
Press flat with a glass dipped in flour on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cookies with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.
Makes 8 cups.

title: "best" chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Put Swiss cheese on top.
Mix soup with wine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cream sugar and margarine until very creamy. Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour three times. Add soda to sour cream; stir well. Add flour and cream alternately to the sugar-margarine mixture. Blend well. Add vanilla, almond extract, butter flavoring and lemon extract. Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into mixture. Pour into well greased, lightly floured loaf pan. Bake for about one and a half hours, or until done.

title: cereal candy
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and add melted white chocolate. Pour in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Break into pieces.

title: clam cakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first.
Mix eggs in bowl and then add clam juice.
Beat eggs and clam juice, then add the milk.
Beat again, then pour into dry ingredients and stir.
Add clams and stir again.
Always stir in same direction.
Heat oil, drop by teaspoon and fry until golden.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Mix remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil in a bowl.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat reserved cake mix, cream cheese, sugar and 3 eggs in mixer bowl for 1 minute. Add milk and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool. Chill until serving time.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles; drain.
Mix tuna, cream of mushroom soup and milk together.
Add noodles and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy turnovers
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour, butter and cream cheese until well blended.
Shape soft dough into a flat ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: honolulu coolers
directions: Fill blender with crushed ice.
Add brandy, Southern Comfort and grenadine.
Fill blender with pineapple juice.
Blend until smooth.
Enjoy.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice and soups in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper pork chops and rub with Kitchen Bouquet. Place pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 to 30 minutes more.

title: stromboli
directions: Cover bread with damp cloth and thaw in refrigerator.
Grease cookie sheet.
Lightly oil dough; press out to edges of cookie sheet.
Spread mustard sparingly on middle third of bread.
Next, layers in order are Mozzarella cheese, hard salami, ham, pepperoni and Swiss cheese.
Fold both sides over and seal all edges.
Place seam-side down on cookie sheet.
Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with oregano or Italian spice.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef or turkey and onion; drain thoroughly.

Combine in large mixing bowl with tortilla, olives, refried beans, jalapeno peppers, grated Monterey Jack cheese and 1 can of enchilada sauce. Spread evenly into 9 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Pour other can of enchilada sauce evenly over top.
Bake or microwave until heated through.
Melt Cheddar cheese on top.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together sugar, flour, cocoa, soda, and salt.
Set aside.
Bring to a boil; butter, oil, and water.
Remove from heat and stir into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ovens vary.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and water.
Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Place rice and soups over chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool until syrupy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mold as desired.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix cheese and eggs together. Saute onion and garlic.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make balls the size of meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach margaret
directions: Thaw spinach and press out liquid.
Crush crackers coarsely. In nonstick pan, melt butter; heat spinach until hot.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Stir egg slightly and scramble among spinach. Cooked egg should show bits of white and yolk.

title: pumpkin cookie bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, nuts and 1 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add butter; mix until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust.
