Bake in slow oven (325°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: zebra country chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from broth and cook egg noodles in broth.
Layer noodles, then chicken, then 1 can mixed veggies and 1/2 can early peas.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over this.
Then pour liquid mixture over all of this.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour (cook covered for 45 minutes and uncovered for the last 15 minutes).
Serve with salad.

title: dream whip fruit salad
directions: Whip Dream Whip according to directions on box; beat in 1/3 cup mayonnaise.
Fold in drained fruits and coconut.
Chill thoroughly or until firm.

title: cheese cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and flour, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into 10 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°. Leave in oven for 1 hour with door open, then leave at room temperature 1/2 hour.
Refrigerate.
Top with cherry pie filling, if desired.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix together the soup and milk, stirring constantly, while hot so it won't stick.
Don't boil the soup.
Add the chopped broccoli and pepper.
Wait one minute, then add butter.
Heat until you see bubbles on the sides and serve.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Place zucchini in a steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut zucchini in half lengthwise; remove pulp, leaving 1/4 inch thick shells.
Dice pulp and set aside; save zucchini shells.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onions and mushrooms; saute until tender.
Stir in diced zucchini pulp, tomato, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring often.
Spoon zucchini mixture evenly into shells; sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange stuffed shells in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes; drain. Place in shallow baking pan.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 400° in gas oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornflake treats
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter in top of double boiler over low heat.
Mix in flavorings and food coloring.
Add cornflakes and stir to gently coat.
Keep in double boiler and drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine dressing, preserves and soup mix.
Mix well.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and cover with dressing mixture.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and cooked thoroughly.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: raisin cream cheese pound cake
directions: Grease pan heavily.
Sprinkle with 6 tablespoons nuts, then lightly with sugar.
Beat butter and cream cheese together until soft.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar, beating until light.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
(Batter may look curdled.) Blend in flour, resifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix in raisins.
Turn into nut-coated pan.

title: cranberry nut loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut and serve.

title: turkey and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter in a large skillet until vegetables are tender; set aside.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cut broccoli spears in half and arrange in a greased shallow casserole.

title: 50th anniversary punch slush
directions: Freeze pineapple juice and set out about an hour before serving.
Add all the ingredients together to make mixture (should be slush).
Serves about 150.

title: sweet potato and banana casserole
directions: Wash sweet potatoes.
Place in a large saucepan.
Cover with boiling water and add salt.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender. Drain potatoes and let cool.
Peel and slice crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter a 2-quart souffle dish or casserole.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add egg and milk; beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Dip franks in batter and fry in hot deep fat until brown on one side, then turn and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with mustard, mayonnaise or catsup.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Day before serving, bake chocolate cake according to directions in large, flat sheet pan.
After cooling, punch holes in the top with the end of wooden spoon.
Then slowly pour Kahlua into those holes.
Let it set overnight in refrigerator.

title: chili-cheese roll
directions: Combine cheese and cream cheese in a large bowl; beat on medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add garlic and pecans; mix well.
Divide mix into equal portions.
Shape each portion into an 8-inch log and roll in chili powder.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: marinated flank steaks
directions: Prick both sides of steaks with fork and place in a large, shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over steaks. Cover; marinate 24 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl (you may need to add more water). Form into balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water until tender. Mash. Saute onion and sweet pepper in butter. Add to eggplant. Add tomatoes. Break up cornbread and add to mixture. Place in baking dish (butter top). Top with shredded cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: german slaw
directions: This recipe should be prepared a day ahead of time.

title: don's peanut butter cake
directions: Mix and cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Mix dates, boiling water and soda.
Cool.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add cooled date mix.
Add sifted dry ingredients and blend well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips, sugar and nuts, which have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until done.

title: pumpkin cheesecake ii
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 tablespoon sugar and melted margarine or butter until blended.
Press onto bottom of 8-inch or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar until well blended.
Beat in pumpkin, spices and salt.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove cake.
Raise oven temperature to 400°.
Mix well sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread over filling.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool cake on rack.
Remove sides of pan and chill cake.
Before serving, garnish with border of whipped cream and/or almonds.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple and juice in a casserole dish.
Combine the sugar, flour and cheese; pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers on top of the sugar mixture and pour melted butter over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: my beef stew
directions: Flour meat; brown in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings, turning until brown.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Cover and let simmer on low 10 minutes.
Add 1 can tomato soup and beef bouillon cubes and water until pot is half full.
Using a pressure cooker, pressure mixture before adding carrots and potatoes.
If not, cook mixture 1 to 2 hours before adding carrots and potatoes on low with lid on to tenderize meat.
After carrots and potatoes have been added and almost done, blend 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Add to pot to thicken mixture and finish cooking.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix and roll in 6 rolls, the size of Hi Ho crackers in diameter.
Sprinkle wax paper lightly with chili powder.

title: chicken burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Divide mixture in half, shaping each portion into a 3/4-inch thick patty.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add patties; cook 5 minutes on each side or until done. Yields 2 servings.

title: strawberry and cream pound cake(low fat)
directions: Slice pound cake into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch loaf pan (can be metal or glass) with sliced pound cake.
Cover the pound cake with half of the Cool Whip.
Wash and slice strawberries and layer over Cool Whip.
Cover the strawberries with the remaining Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour.
Chilling allows the fruit to settle and the Cool Whip to set for easier serving.
Serves approximately 12, based on size of slices.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Add pineapple.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nutmeats.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: posse stew
directions: In a skillet, brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, chilies, hominy and corn; season with salt and pepper. Combine cornstarch and water, then stir into stew.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: corn and rice salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine corn, pepper, rice, onion and olives. Combine remaining ingredients (except tomatoes and cheese).
Mix well and pour over corn mixture.
Cover.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Before serving mix in tomatoes.
Top with cheese.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in oiled skillet.
Layer potatoes, onions and pork chops in greased baking dish, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Cover with mixture of Worcestershire sauce, soup and milk.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes, or until chops are very tender.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: rolled wheat clusters
directions: Boil butter, milk, sugar and salt for two minutes and pour over remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix and drop.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix liquids first.
Do not use electric mixer.

title: potato chip casserole
directions: Cut up potatoes and cook in boiling water until tender.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and cooked potatoes.
Place mixture in a casserole dish.
Top mixture with grated Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: frangipan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° with rack in middle. Grease and flour tart pan (or small cake pan). With electric mixer on low speed, blend almond paste, sugar and butter. Continue mixing, adding eggs one at a time. Mix on high until batter is light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Stir in cake flour. Gently fold into batter until just blended. Spread batter evenly into pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden and inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Spread with thin frosting or preserves.

title: french bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and beans.
Line bottom of greased dish with mixture. Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and water chestnuts.
Layer next. Melt oleo and pour over crushed Ritz crackers.
Mix together and put on top.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Can be made and put in refrigerator overnight before baking.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip, drained pineapple and 8 crushed cookies.
Sprinkle the top with 8 more crushed cookies.

title: rice with pimento
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour covered and then 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Place butter in marshmallows in a 12 x 7 1/2-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave on Full power 2 minutes.
Stir to combine. Microwave on Full power 2 minutes longer.
Stir until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly in dish.
Cut in squares when cool.
Yield:
15 squares.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: On a round dish layer ingredients in the order given.
Garnish with chips around the edges.

title: ritz cracker cake
directions: Mix together egg whites, baking powder and sugar with mixer, then stir in the crackers, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip when cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Slightly grease an 8 x 8-inch pan or larger.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until brown.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Saute meat in skillet with onions; drain.
Mix eggs, cornmeal, milk, oil, soda, salt and corns.
Place 1/2 of mixture in pan, then spread meat/onions on top.
Spread cheese. Pour remaining cornbread mix and sprinkle jalapenos on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: company potatoes
directions: Place hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Top with corn flakes and drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb cheese bread
directions: Mix together butter, onion, mustard, lemon juice, poppy seeds and Beau Monde.
Slice bread diagonally (do not cut all the way through); put a slice of Swiss cheese in each cut.
Place in an aluminum foil boat.
Do not cover.
Spread generously with seasoned butter spread.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
In a large bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Add salt and blend well.
Add egg, mixing well.
Add remaining water and stir well.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in greased bowl and set aside until doubled in bulk.
Dough may be punched down several times.
Roll out on floured surface and form into rolls.
Place rolls in buttered pans and butter tops.
Let rise again.
Bake at 425° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: frankly potato stew
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes in small amount of boiling water.
Drain.
Meanwhile, heat butter in a large skillet and saute onions.
Add sliced hot dogs, tomatoes (with juice), paprika, salt, caraway seed and potatoes.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes to heat through and blend flavors.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: liver cake for dogs
directions: Trim liver and remove gristle.
Cut into small pieces and puree in blender.
Pour into a bowl and add cornmeal and garlic salt.
Blend well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
(If you want a thinner cake, use cookie sheet.) Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Cut into squares (like brownies).
Wrap each piece in foil and freeze.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; add next four ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Place 1/2 cup of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan; place a layer of tortillas on top (4 for each layer overlapping), then a layer of sauce mixture, then cheese.
Repeat layers after completing second layer.
Add sour cream.
Add last layer and bake at 350° for 25 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Place water, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and food coloring in a pot.
Cook until boiling; add butter.
Peel and slice 6 apples. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk. Roll out onto lightly floured board.
Cut dough into 6 (6-inch) squares.
Place apples on dough and sprinkle generously with cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg.
Also place a dab of butter on them. Fold corners into center and pinch seams closed.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour the sugar syrup over dumplings and sprinkle generously with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: layered pea salad
directions: In large clear glass bowl, layer according to the following: lettuce, diced onions, shredded cheddar cheese, lettuce, eggs, lettuce, bacon, shredded cheddar cheese, chopped ham, and peas. For top layer, mix Miracle Whip and sugar and spread evenly over top of salad.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Pour into muffin pans.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Makes 6.
You can double recipe.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and potatoes.
Scald milk and butter together.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour in crust and bake at 350° until pie is done.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Cool and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: the dish
directions: Saute the ground meat, onions and bell peppers.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased covered dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook frozen broccoli and arrange in baking dish. Top with cooked chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Pour over ingredients. Top with cheese. Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli and onions.
Just before serving, add croutons, bacon bits and dressing.

title: rice with corn and carrots
directions: Soak rice in hot water for 5 minutes, rinse well and drain. Meanwhile, in a blender, puree the onion and garlic in 1/2 cup water and set aside.
Heat 1/2-inch oil in a large skillet, add the rice and saute until the grains separate and become translucent, about 5 minutes.
Pour off excess oil.
Add the carrots and stir for 2 minutes.
Add the 4 cups hot water and salt.
When the water comes to a boil, add the corn.
Stir, cover, and cook over medium-low heat for 20 to 30 minutes or until the water is absorbed and the rice is tender.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter until light.
Add egg, sugar and vanilla.
Beat. Add dry ingredients.
Add applesauce.
Beat on high speed. Blend in pecans and dates.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco layer dip
directions: Put refried beans in bottom of spring-form pan.
Brown hamburger, bouillon and green olives; drain and cool.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Put hamburger mixture on beans when cool.
Then layer sour cream mixture.
Top with avocado dip.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Garnish, serve with chips.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar
and
water; boil 10 minutes.
Completely cool syrup,
then
add
berries.
Save some whole strawberries for garnish when serving sauce over ice cream or pudding.

title: party puffs
directions: Cream the cheese and butter.
Work in sifted flour mixed with baking powder and salt.
Pat into a roll and put in refrigerator for at least a half hour.
Roll out very thin and cut with a small round cutter.
Spread (sparingly) half-circle with marmalade and fold over other half.
Bake a few minutes until brown in a 450° oven.

title: joe's favorite
directions: In Dutch oven, brown and crumble bacon.
Add onion and ground beef (turkey will work, too).
Brown; add pepper and soy sauce. Layer sliced potatoes over meat.
Scatter celery slices over potatoes.
Arrange tomato slices over all.
Arrange pepper rings over tomatoes.
Put cabbage on top.
Pour 1/2 cup water over all. Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat to low/simmer for approximately 15 minutes.

title: chicken taco salad
directions: Mix together seasoning, soup and sour cream. Put chicken in greased glass baking dish; cover with soup mixture. Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Sprinkle with taco mix and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Mix together chopped onions, diced tomatoes, diced avocados, kidney beans and Italian dressing.
Marinate one hour, then add hamburger mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: hash browns
directions: Boil potatoes until cooked.
Shred enough to measure 4 cups. Toss potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Heat butter and oil in 10-inch skillet.
Pack potato mixture firmly in skillet, leaving a 1/2-inch space around edge.
Cook over low heat until bottom crust is brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut potato mixture into fourths; turn.
Add 1 tablespoon oil if necessary.
Cook until brown, 12 to 15 minutes longer.

title: pigeon peas and rice
directions: Cook smoked bacon until crisp.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper.
Saute until soft.
Add pigeon peas and tomato sauce along with salt, pepper and thyme.
Stir well.
Add water and rice. Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt, then cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat together vinegar, water and egg.
Mix with flour mixture until dough is moist enough to form a ball.
Wrap in plastic and chill for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 large double crust pie.

title: stained glass church window candy
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat. Add egg; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Place marshmallows and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour chocolate mix over marshmallows and nuts. Mix well.
Divide mix in half on waxed paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Shape each half in a roll approximately 8-inches long.
Chill several hours.
Slice to serve.

title: hopping john
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight; drain.
Cover beans with water. Add ham bone and bacon; cook until beans are soft.
Add rice and salt and pepper.
Cook rapidly for 20 minutes.
Lower heat and steam for 30 minutes.

title: my mother's fresh corn custard
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter; set aside. Scald milk in double boiler over hot water; add cheese and stir until melted. Remove from heat and slowly pour over beaten eggs, beating constantly. Add seasonings, sauteed vegetables, crumbs, mushrooms and corn. Mix well; pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Place in pan of hot water in oven and bake slowly at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in stew pot until brown.
Remove bacon; add green pepper, onions, celery, garlic, black, red and white pepper and salt.
Saute for 10 minutes on medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add cabbage, Ro-Tel tomatoes and bacon.
Cook 1 hour on medium heat, covered, stirring occasionally.
Hot!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together with potatoes.

title: no fat soup
directions: Stir package of Beefy Onion soup into 4 or 5 cups of hot water.
Add lots of carrots, onion and celery.
Let it cook a while.
Add lots of cabbage, salt and pepper and 2 cubes of chicken bouillon or 1 tablespoon of powdered type.
Cook 1 hour. Add 1 cup of egg noodles a few minutes before it's done.
You may need to add more water as it cooks.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with the milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a layer of graham crackers on the bottom. Cover with 1/2 of pudding mixture, then add another layer of graham crackers.
Spread with remaining pudding, then add another layer of graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Put all in large baking pan with lid. Bake 5 hours at 250°. Don't peek.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Spread crumbs (save some for top) over bottom of long Pyrex pan.
Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Carefully spread this mixture over crumbs.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold in drained pineapple. Spread over butter-sugar layer.
Cover with crumbs lightly.
Cover and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and make into small cocktail balls; brown. Pour barbecue sauce over and bake at 350° until hot. Serve on toothpicks.

title: cranberry relish(from the greenbrier resort, west virginia)
directions: Chop or grind fruit (medium blade).
Add sugar, lemon juice and jam.
Let set overnight.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers; cook in boiling water
for 5 minutes.
Brown beef and cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in soup and remaining ingredients.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread 1/2 pie filling in bottom of pan. Bake 15 minutes until brown.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Remove from oven.
Beat sugars, eggs, vanilla and cream cheese until smooth; pour over hot cherry pie filling.
Bake 25 minutes, they will be slightly soft in center.
Cool completely; fill center with remaining pie filling.

title: holiday liver pat
directions: Mix liverwurst, half of the cream cheese, onion, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Combine well.
Form a mound of pate in the center of a serving dish; place in the freezer for 15 minutes.
Frost with the remaining cream cheese.
Slice a few stuffed olives with pimentos so the green is a circle on the outside with the red pimento on the inside.
Arrange them on the outside of the mound as a garnish.
Serve anytime (not just for holidays) with low-carb crackers and veggies.

title: haddock barrie
directions: Wash and dry fillets.
Coat with seasoned flour.
Use 1/2 of the butter to grease a shallow dish and arrange fillets.
Melt remaining butter.
Stir in flour to make a paste.
Add milk to make a white sauce.
Add cheese and blend.
Add sauteed onion and celery and cut up shrimp.
Pour over fish fillets and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: In large bowl, put cottage cheese, dry package of jello, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Mix together and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: nacho chicken
directions: Crush chips and put in bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Mix onion, chicken, soups, tomatoes and broth.
Pour over chips. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: *favorite apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry for a double crust pie.
On a lightly floured board, roll out half to a 12-inch round.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Trim overhang to 1/2-inch.
Mix granulated and brown sugars, flour, spices and salt in a small bowl.
Spread about 1/3 of the apples into prepared pastry shell.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of the sugar and spice mixture.
Repeat layering 2 more times.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, flour and cocoa; mix well. Add nuts. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. While brownies are hot, put marshmallow cream on top. Put filling on top of marshmallow cream when cooled.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Spread crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan until smooth. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat the eggs; add milk, sugar, and spice.
Pour liquid over the bread in a 1-1/2 qt. casserole, let stand until thoroughly soaked.
Add raisins if desired.
Bake 20-40 minutes or until firm in a moderate oven, 350°.
Serve with milk, jelly or any "pudding" sauce.
I serve this with maple syrup and it tastes like French Toast.
Shallow pan might take 20 minutes.
Deeper dish takes about 40-45 minutes.
Check on a regular basis.
Double recipe for a 9 X 13 dish.

title: liver mush
directions: Wash meat. Cover with water. Cook until done. Grind meat or put in a food processor on puree with cooking liquid.
Return to pot. Add salt, sage, thyme, red pepper and black pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil. Slowly add corn meal and flour.
Cook until done.

title: texas straw hat
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Add water and taco seasoning and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If mixture becomes dry, add more water. Serve 1/3 cup taco meat and 1/4 cup of cheese over 3/4 cup of corn chips.
Add diced tomatoes and shredded lettuce.

title: heart-smart cocoa kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
At high speed, gradually beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
At low speed, beat in cocoa and almond extract.
Fold in almonds.
Drop mixture by slightly rounded tablespoonful onto cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set.
Cool on cookie sheets 10 minutes; loosen with metal spatula.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: patty's shrimp trash
directions: Put vegetables and shrimp in glass container and cover with Italian dressing.
Sprinkle generously with dill seed.
Allow mixture to marinate (covered) in refrigerator for at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Gently stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into bottoms of 8 ounce paper or plastic cups. Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
If desired, decorate with gummy worms or gumdrop flowers to resemble flowerpots.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Bring butter, sugar and Karo to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in extract and soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Mix well.

title: fruit salad(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Drain all of the fruit and sprinkle the pudding over it.
Stir it up a little. Add the orange juice and a small amount of the juice. Stir it up more. If you like it thinner, you can add more juice.

title: toll house cookie pie
directions: Melt butter in microwave, then cool.
Add eggs, flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add walnuts and chocolate chips. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pat a pie crust
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well.
Add sugar.
Whip salad oil and milk, then add to flour mixture.
Pat in dish and bake.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix ingredients well and put on burger buns. Wrap in foil. Place in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and burgers are hot.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef, onions and peppers.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add soup, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Add the first 8 ingredients; beat with mixer until well creamed.
Stir in crabmeat.
Put into a 1 1/4-quart casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: raspberry apple jello
directions: Dissolve hot water in Jell-O.
Mix and add lemon juice and applesauce.
Pour in a flat pan.
Serve on lettuce and nice wedge of Jell-O.

title: lazy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan the flour and milk; add melted margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour over soup mixture.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: lime or lemon congealed salad
directions: Mix jello, water and fruit in a bowl and stir well.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and cheese together. Add to jello mixture.
Mix well and pour into a long dish and chill overnight.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with flour.
Cream together butter and 2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, blending well, then sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold the dry ingredients into creamed mixture and beat until just blended.
Do not overbeat.
In a separate bowl mix remaining 3/4 cup sugar with pecans and cinnamon.
Pour half of batter into Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with half of sugar mixture.
Add remaining batter and top with rest of sugar mixture.
Bake 60 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm.
Serves 10 portions.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in rectangular pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until top browns.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla and Mazola.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well with first mixture.
Fold in nuts.

title: liz's pie
directions: Add baking powder to egg whites, then sugar and crackers.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into well-greased pie pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Sprinkle few pecans on top.

title: creamed parsnips
directions: Peel, cut up and core parsnips.
Cook until tender in salted boiling water or steam them.
Mash with butter and cream over a low heat.
Heat creamed parsnips through and add seasoning.

title: ring-tum diddy
directions: Add tomato soup to onions.
Heat until bubbly; stir often.
Add cheese.
Stir constantly until smooth.
Add egg and stir quickly until blended.
Serve over saltines.
Recipe can easily be doubled or tripled.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix ground beef, chopped onion, poultry seasoning, raw rice, pepper and salt; form mixture into small balls (about the size of walnuts).
Brown lightly in uncovered pan in oil; drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cover tightly; simmer for 45 to 50 minutes, or until rice is tender.

title: sharon's sweet potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine sweet potatoes (cubed), onion and broth. Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender. Take half and puree in a blender or food processor (take care not to splash hot liquid). Return to saucepan. Stir in apple juice, thyme and pepper. Season to taste with salt. Heat thoroughly. Stir in half and half or milk.

title: coconut pineapple deep dish pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, eggs, margarine and pineapple. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Cook in 350° oven until done, about 45 minutes.
To make a regular sized pie, cut portions in half.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Combine butter, cream and cheese and cook over low heat until cheese melts and cream bubbles and thickens. Add parsley. Serves 4.

title: honey sugar pecans
directions: Combine and stir until dissolved first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat to 242° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and pecans.
Stir gently until it becomes creamy. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cream cheese and mix with electric mixer or blender.
Blend well.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Place in oblong dish and chill approximately 35 to 40 minutes in refrigerator.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Add pineapple and nuts to slightly thickened jello.
Return to refrigerator to set until firm enough to serve.

title: walnut rolls
directions: Blend flour, salt and butter as for pie crust.
Combine yeast, sugar and warm milk and let rest until yeast is softened.
Then make well in center of flour mixture and add yeast mixture and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
(Dough will be soft.)
Make five balls from dough mixture.
(Dough does not have to rise.)

title: denim dumpling dinner(serves 12)
directions: Simmer chickens in 6 cups water and 1 tablespoon salt until tender.
Remove chicken from bones, leaving in large pieces.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; drain and cool and cut up. Cook spaghetti in broth. Saute peppers and onions. Mix chicken, spaghetti, peppers and onions. Add Ro-Tel and cheese. Stir and cover. Heat until cheese is melted. Stir well and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter; add onions and saute.
Add corn, milk, egg, pimento and cracker crumbs.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: salad dressing
directions: Peel garlic and slice thin.
Put all in jar and stir or shake to mix.

title: frickadilly burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Form into patties.
Great on a grill!

title: cream cheese mints
directions: *Can use mint, lemon, orange, almond, rum or butter flavorings.
For chocolate mints, add 6 teaspoons cocoa and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer ingredients in an 8x8 dish in order listed.
Chill for an hour or two to set up.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Great picnic food.

title: stuffing
directions: Mix well and add to bread crumbs.
Add more milk if needed.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot.
Drain.
Add onions and garlic. Then add green chilies, seasonings, tomato paste, broth/bouillon and beans.
Bring to a boil; lower heat to simmer.
Cover and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: In a saucepan, saute the mushrooms, garlic, onions, nutmeg, parsley and pepper in the olive oil until the mushrooms soften and release their liquid.
Sprinkle with the flour and cook.
Stir for 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in the stock.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Unroll dough and put on an 11 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Press edges and seams to form solid layer of dough.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, salad dressing mix and milk; beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables and meat over cream cheese. Refrigerate and cut into desired pieces.

title: unsugar cheesecake(diabetic)
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Blend with 1/2 cup of milk. Blend in remaining milk and pudding mix.
Pour into crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into spring-form pan. In mixer, cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and the vanilla.
Spoon into crust and bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Take out immediately.
Beat together sour cream and lemon juice.
Spread this on top of cheesecake and bake 5 minutes at 500°.
Take out immediately.
Chill overnight.
Spoon can of pie mix over cake and garnish with nuts.

title: grandmother's hurry up pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix sugar and flour so as to mix well and add to eggs.
Beat until smooth and add milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into casserole and bake at 350° until it does not shake like liquid.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Makes about 1 quart. Best if served next day.
Refrigerate.

title: potatoes in tuxedos
directions: Select very small, round potatoes.
Clean potatoes; leave skins on.
Boil just until done.
Chill.
Scoop out top portion of each potato.
Fill with 1 tablespoon sour cream.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and cayenne pepper.
Garnish each potato with a sprig of parsley.
Serve chilled.
Makes 6 appetizer servings or 2 potatoes per serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put 1/4 stick butter in casserole dish and let it melt while oven is heating up.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour into dish.
Add 1 large can sliced peaches (minus juice).
Bake 30 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions; drain.
In a 2 qt. saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, or until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese until melted.
Turn macaroni into greased 2 qt. casserole.
Pour cheese mixture over macaroni; mix well.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Bake at 375° oven for 25 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter, butter and graham cracker crumbs together.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt package of chocolate chips.
Spread on top.
Refrigerate and cut into small squares.

title: red snapper veracruz
directions: Prick the fish on both sides with a fork.
Place in a glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and lime juice.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: no bake peanut butter delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top. Refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: lanettina
directions: Wash pigs feet.
Cover with slightly salted water.
Add several minced garlic cloves and pepper to taste.
Boil until the meat will slip from bones.
Place some meat in individual serving bowls and pour strained broth over top.
Chill until firm.
Serve with bread.

title: meat balls
directions: Soak bread in water 2 to 3 minutes.
Squeeze out moisture.
Mix bread with all other ingredients. Shape in about 20 balls.
Brown in hot oil.
Add to sauce and cook 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: west virginia special
directions: Fry onion and beef together.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour corn bread over the top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: peanut butter sundae topping
directions: Cook until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add a chunk of butter. Serve over ice cream for a delicious treat.

title: easy squash pickles
directions: Heat. Drop squash into hot solution. Let come to boil. Pack and seal.

title: spicy peach mold
directions: Drain peaches and reserve juice. Mix spices with sugar. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add combined sugar and spices, using whisk to mix.
Pour in vinegar and peach juice and allow to thicken slightly. Add peaches and refrigerate until time to serve. An interesting addition to a baked ham dinner.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake at 300° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: three potato gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 3-quart shallow baking dish In bowl, combine cream with mustard, cornstarch, salt and pepper. Toss into sliced potatoes.
Pour into dish and cover.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.
Sprinkle with thyme.

title: stuffed cabbage soup
directions: Brown stew meat in oil.
Add coleslaw mix and onion.
Cook, covered, 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, beef broth, water, brown sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a boil. Add rice.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In 400° oven, bake in 13 x 9-inch pan the chicken breasts for 20 minutes.
Remove breasts from pan.
Pour 2 cups boiling water into pan.

Add 2 chicken bouillon cubes and stir until dissolved. Add minced onion (optional) and converted rice; spread evenly. Place chicken breasts on top of rice (other side up) and return to oven for 40 minutes.
(Check in 30 to 35 minutes as you might have to add more liquid.)
Enjoy!

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 30 minutes.
Serve on crackers of choice.

title: airy cheese pancakes
directions: Rub cottage cheese through a sieve (tomato strainer works well, too) into a bowl.
Stir egg yolks into the cheese.
Add matzo meal and salt; mix well with spoon.
Beat egg whites with mixer in separate bowl until stiff; fold cheese mixture into egg whites.

title: cheese bread
directions: Add margarine to mayonnaise and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Spread over bread and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Slice diagonally.
Serve hot.
Very good.

title: skillet beef enchilada
directions: Brown beef with onion in large skillet, about 5 minutes.
Add beans, broth, taco mix and corn.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve with tortillas. Serves 4.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar and beat in eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternately with yogurt.
Mix well, then add pears.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sopa de ajo
directions: In a saucepan, saut garlic in olive oil. In the same oil, fry bread. Set aside. Remove 2 tablespoons of oil. Return the garlic in the saucepan and pour in 6 cups broth. When it begins to boil, stir in beaten eggs. Season according to taste. Just before serving, drop in the fried bread or croutons.

title: spanish bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 17 x 12-inch cookie sheet.
In a 2-quart pan, heat raisins, shortening and water; bring to a boil (but not rolling) for 20 minutes.
In another large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
While hot, add liquid (raisin) mixture into dry mixture; blend and pour into cookie sheet.
Bake to golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar or a cream cheese frosting (icing).

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good served with a chicken entree.

title: hot rice dish
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add onion, green pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Simmer until tender.
Add rice, sage, salt and pepper; mix well.
Serve hot.
Especially good with fowl and pork.

title: turkey schoitzet
directions: Preheat oven at 400°. Whip egg white with 1 teaspoon water. Pound turkey slices until tenderized, about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thin. Dip in egg white, then in bread crumbs. Place on lightly oiled baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes; turn over. Bake 5 minutes or until brown and crispy. Serve with cranberry sauce on the side.

title: chicken with salsa
directions: *In choosing which salsa to use, remember that salsa becomes milder when cooked.

title: chile con queso
directions: Saute sausage in frying pan, drain.
Add garlic and onion and saute.
Add tomatoes, mash and cook down.
Mix flour and milk into a paste and add to sausage mixture.
When it is thickened a little, add the chiles, salt and cheese.
When the cheese has melted, pour the mixture into a chafing dish and serve with tortilla chips.

title: beth's brownies
directions: Prepare
brownies
according
to package, then add sour cream and chocolate chips;
mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into 13	x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake according to package instructions.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: easy do pralines
directions: Combine ingredients, except pecans.
Cook slowly until dissolved.
Add pecans.
Boil slowly until candy thermometer registers 235° to 240° or until candy forms soft ball.
Remove from heat and beat until mixture thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Yields 15 (4-inch) patties.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, green onions, tomatoes and eggs.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together the first five ingredients.
Add pecans.
Place in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, drain.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Combine with bacon and rest of ingredients.
Bake uncovered in a large casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tater sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well and refrigerate.

title: pineapple coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in pineapple.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend well into shortening mixture.
Stir in coconut.
Cover and chill dough 2 hours or more.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated oven 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool cookies on rack.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: grilled bacon franks
directions: Combine in a bowl mustard, catsup and minced onion.
Swirl 2 slices of bacon around frankfurters, covering completely.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Grease grill lightly.
Brush frankfurters with 1/2 mustard mixture.
Cook frankfurters on grill, turning frequently, until bacon is crisp.
Spread rolls with butter, placing butter side down on grill until brown.
Remove rolls and frankfurters to a platter.
Brush rolls with remaining sauce. Serve in rolls.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix everything except chips. Pat chips in last by hand.
Pour into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with oil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Crush 1 cup of the fresh strawberries and cook with water for about 2 minutes.
Sieve pulp into separate bowl; discard.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; stir into berry juice.
Cool and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Place 1 1/2 cup fresh strawberries in baked and cooled pastry shell.
Pour half of the sauce over strawberries.
Repeat layers with another 1 1/2 cups strawberries and remaining sauce.
Chill.

title: rabbit with abbey-beer
directions: Burnish the pieces of rabbit (with salt and pepper) in butter. Add the beer, water and vinegar.
Add the cut onion, sugar, thyme and laurel.
Let it all simmer for about 1 hour.
Thicken the sauce with the maizena. Serve with boiled potatoes and apple compote.

title: zingy bean dip
directions: Whip all ingredients in food processor.
Serve with tortilla chips or pita crisps or vegetable dippers such as pepper strips and celery sticks.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place desired amount of apples in 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Melt stick of butter in pan; mix oats, flour and sugar with melted butter in dish.
Cover apples with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out dough covering baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread over crust.
Add vegetables.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased rectangle casserole until golden brown at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into beaten eggs and roll into seasoned bread crumbs. Brown in hot oil and margarine.
Place in a large casserole dish. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and pour spaghetti sauce on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat together butter and brown sugar.
Add molasses.
Beat. Add soda to buttermilk.
Add to other ingredients.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Combine remaining dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients to make a soft dough.
Roll in balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar. stir in chocolate syrup, vegetable oil and vanilla extract.
Then combine both bowls and mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch square greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Stir in peanut butter. Mix in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips. Press together into small balls. Put on cookie sheet and press with fingertips. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put the peanut butter in the bowl and sugar, butter, 2 cups of flour, mix oil, vanilla.
Then stir and put in a pan.
When through, put it in the oven and bake at 350°.
When cookies are through, put on a nice dish.
They'll be ready to serve.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, onions, bacon and cauliflower.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour on top. Cover.
Toss the next day.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Melt cheese in Ro-Tel in saucepan (don't scorch).
Put in crock-pot on low heat.
Grate over toast, buns, etc. or use as a dip with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bring syrup, spread and sugar to boil in 2-quart saucepan.
Boil gently, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Place pecans in pastry shell.
Beat eggs, vanilla and salt in large bowl.
Gradually stir in cooled syrup mixture.
Pour over pecans in pastry shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Grease baking sheet and preheat oven to 425°.
Place cool water into small bowl and beat in egg.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix only 2 cups of the white flour, wheat flour, yeast and salt.
Add water, honey and oil (in this order).
Stir with a wooden spoon until combined.
Add enough of the set aside flour to make a soft dough.
Knead dough about 5 to 7 minutes.
Cut dough into 12 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a rope.
Form pretzels and place on baking sheet.
Dough will contract a little, so enlarge holes with finger.
Brush each pretzel with your egg mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Roll and chill until you get your chocolate ready.
You can buy 1 pound bags of chocolate at the candy store.
It takes 1 1/2 pounds for 1 batch or 3 pounds for 2 batches.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Add garlic salt, salt and pepper to egg and beat together. Pour this mixture over the ground beef and bread crumbs and mix well. Form into small meatballs and cook over medium heat, turning often to brown all sides. Drain grease from meatballs. Add the can of mushroom soup and 1 can of water to the meatballs. Cover and simmer on low for 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown salt and peppered chops, then set aside.
Layer potatoes and sauce (made of soup, water, sour cream & parsley) in an 8x8 casserole dish.
Lay chops on top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hr. 15 mins.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Note:
Recipe is fairly hot.
Less cayenne pepper may be used.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain. Stir in barbecue sauce and brown sugar. Line muffin tin with a biscuit. Dip meat mixture into each cup and top with shredded cheese. Bake at 375° until biscuits are browned and cheese is melted.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 380° oven 25 to 30 minutes. (Line bottom of square pan with wax paper; grease pan.) After removing from oven, let stay in pan 5 minutes.
Then cut in finger lengths.
Turn over on board or wax paper.
Remove wax paper from bottom and cool.
Roll each piece in confectioners sugar.

title: pecan delight
directions: Combine.
Fold in egg whites gradually.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: perkins family's original macaroni casserole
directions: Note:
The ingredients above will require a 5-quart oven Corning Ware casserole.
When you get the hang of it you can use what suits you best.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli with onion and cook as directed on broccoli package.
Drain. Combine vegetables with remaining ingredients. Pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Melt butter in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add flour and dash of salt.
Stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add egg and beat vigorously until smooth.
Stir in cheese.

title: crouton strata
directions: Put croutons in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage. Drain and sprinkle on top of croutons. Add the cheese over the sausage. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over the cheese mixture in the pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: waffles divan
directions: Microwave cream cheese on High 30 seconds or until softened. Stir in soup until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High 4 minutes; stir once during heating.
Serve over waffles. Garnish with chopped tomato.
Makes 4 servings.

title: the best strawberry pie
directions: Place sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Boil water, sugar, jello and cornstarch until thick.
Cool for 20 minutes.
After cooling, add Grand Marnier and mix well.
Pour over berries and top with whipped cream.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all
ingredients, mixing well.	Roll into balls the size of
walnut.
Freeze.
Before serving, place on cookie sheet still frozen.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: white frosting
directions: Beat the egg whites.
Boil the first 3 ingredients.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour mixture into beaten egg whites; mix until very stiff.

title: pears poached in port
directions: In saucepan just large enough to fit pears, mix sugar, water, cinnamon, cloves and orange peel.
Bring to low boil for a few minutes; cool.
Peel pears, leaving stems.
Cut small bit off bottom so pears will stand upright.
Leave them in a bowl, covered with mild salt water until ready to cook.
Drain pears; place into syrup pan.
Add Port; bring to gentle boil.
Turn down to simmer. Cover; cook, occasionally spooning syrup over pears, until tender but not mushy (about 15 minutes).
Serve each pear upright and spoon syrup over.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa over low heat.
Cool; add eggs (well beaten) and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: crostata
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients and mix well. Knead gently on floured surface until smooth.
(Or mix all of the above in a food processor.)
Set aside 1/3 of the dough.
On floured surface, roll remaining dough to 15 x 10-inch rectangle. Place on ungreased cookie sheet or pan.
Spread each jam crosswise over 1/3 of the dough in pan.
Roll remaining dough to 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Carefully form strips into lattice top diagonally over jam-topped dough.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 40 bars.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Stir in flour and peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and sift confectioners sugar on top.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: date balls
directions: In saucepan, add butter, sugar, dates and eggs.
Cook until melted; add vanilla.
Pour over Rice Krispies and nuts.
Let cool; roll into balls, then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: unnamed delight
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Pour butter over crackers.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Add pecans and coconut.
Add chocolate chips (do not stir).
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until coconut is brown.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add seasoning mix and simmer.
Add sauce, beans and chillies.
Grease a large oblong baking dish. Make first layer with three tortillas, half the meat sauce and half the cheese.
Repeat and make the second layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Blend first 9 ingredients, adjusting to your own taste.
Slice off top of Hawaiian bread and hollow out the inside, reserving bread for dipping.
Place the chicken-ham mixture inside the bread shell.
Place 4 to 5 pineapple rings on top of the dip. Place cherries inside of pineapple rings.
Place the top of bread you previously sliced off back in place, until ready to serve. Cut each of the buns in fourths.
Place near dip for additional dipping.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all these ingredients well and pour into an ungreased long pan . Bake at 350°
until done.
Leave in pan.

title: nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together next 3 ingredients and beat hard for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour this mixture on top of crust layer in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Cover bottom of crust with ripe sliced peaches. Combine other ingredients and pour over peaches. Pat rim of pie crust with milk. Bake at 400° until crust is brown (about 19 minutes).
Reduce heat to 300°. Bake until done, about 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Cook at 325° (in long pan) for 1 1/2 hours.
Great dessert with coffee.

title: fall harvest rice
directions: Cook sausage in skillet, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Combine sausage, rice, apple, onion, celery, raisins, sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon and pepper; spoon into buttered 2 qt. baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salad supreme(english pea salad)
directions: Put in layers in order the first 5 ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon chips. Chill and toss before serving.
To keep salad from getting soggy, turn a saucer upside-down in bottom of salad bowl.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix in next 3 ingredients.
Completely cover with biscuits.
Put into oven and bake until biscuits are brown.

title: french bread(serves 100)
directions: Slice, cut bread into 3/8-inch slices.
Dip into egg and milk mixture, just long enough to wet the slices.
Drain off excess milk then drop slices into deep cooking oil (340° to 350°) and fry until bread becomes slightly browned.

title: banana pineapple pudding cake
directions: Mix together sugar, cinnamon and crumbs; combine with margarine.
Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat Dream Whip, pudding and milk until stiff; pour half over crumb mixture. Add bananas and pineapple.
Top with remaining pudding mixture. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Cream well the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese. Frost with Cool Whip and top with nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: ruth hough's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in casserole and top with noodles.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order and bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour or in gas oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple dumpling cake
directions: Mix all except brown sugar and 2 cups water with mixer on low until moistened.
Mix on high speed 2 minutes.
Bring brown sugar and 2 cups water to boil in a small saucepan.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer apples and raisins.
Spread cake mix over apples and raisins.
Pour sugar water mixture over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind all vegetables in food chopper or processor.
Mix with salt.
Put in bag and hang on line overnight.
Mix with vinegar, molasses or brown sugar, sugar, dry mustard and pickling spices tied in cheesecloth bag.
Bring to boil and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Seal in sterile jars.
Makes 20 to 22 pints.

title: yum yum coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients alternately with sour cream to which soda has been added.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover batter with pie filling and cut into batter with a knife.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: peach icebox pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together until thickened. Add peaches and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip last.
Put in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill several hours or overnight.
May be frozen.

title: chili salad
directions: Cook ground chuck, onion and green pepper in microwave.
Put meat mixture in a large skillet on medium-high heat and add kidney beans, hot sauce, tomato sauce, salt, black pepper and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer until thick. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Mix with lettuce.

title: spinach lasagna(serves 6)
directions: Open spinach box and cook (in box) in microwave for 4 minutes. Press out water.
Blend the 3 cheeses and seasonings; set aside. Spray an 11 x 7-inch pan with a nonstick spray.
Spoon about 1/2 cup pasta sauce in bottom of pan.
Put in 3 noodles.
Spoon about 1/2 of cheese mixture on noodles.
Put drained spinach on cheese mixture.
Spoon about 1/2 of pasta sauce on spinach.
Add 3 more noodles, remaining cheese mixture and remaining pasta sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until noodles pierce easily with fork.
Uncover; top with Mozzarella cheese and bake another 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: bow tie pasta
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender. Cut into chunks; brown in vegetable oil. Add alfredo sauce and tomato sauce. Simmer a few minutes, then add mixture to cooked pasta. Stir until mixed well. Add salt, if desired.

title: easy corn sausage souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into large deep casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: heather heffner's breakfast casserole
directions: Press potatoes between paper towel to remove excess moisture. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes evenly in bottom. Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven until brown around edges. Remove from oven; let stand until slightly cool (10 minutes). Reduce temperature to 350°.
Layer ham and cheeses on top of the potatoes.
Combine eggs and cream.
Pour over mixture in pan. Bake, uncovered, about 25 minutes or until center sets.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stayabed stew
directions: In 3-quart casserole, mix everything together and cover. Bake in 275° oven for 5 hours.
It will cook by itself and be done in 5 hours.
Serves 4.

title: lazy ladies
directions: Put 1 1/2 sticks margarine in a pan with sauerkraut and sprinkle on pepper.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes. Add mushroom soup. Cook another 5 to 10 minutes. Cook noodles until soft.
Drain and rinse in warm water.
Add 1/4 stick margarine to warm noodles. Stir until melted. Add sauerkraut and soup mixture; serve immediately.

title: spinach patties
directions: Cook spinach partially; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until cold.
Form into patties.
Put on greased pan. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: noodle pudding souffle
directions: Beat egg yolks; add melted butter and sugar.
Fold in cottage cheese, sour cream and noodles.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in a 2-quart buttered casserole and sprinkle top with crushed corn flakes.
Dot generously with butter.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: baked potato salad with hot dogs
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk all at once; stir over medium heat until mixture thickens. Boil 1 minute and remove from heat; blend in mayonnaise, potatoes, beans, onion and all but 6 hot dog slices.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole; top with buttered bread crumbs and extra hot dog slices.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and put in a large bowl.
Fry onion until soft; add to bacon.
Fry ground beef or ground turkey; drain and discard fat.
Add cooked meat to remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana cream cheese icing
directions: Beat the cream cheese and oleo until fluffy.
Add banana and 1/2 box 10x sugar; mix well.
Add chopped nuts and 1/2 box 10x sugar.
Beat until smooth and cover completely cooled cake.

title: angel delight
directions: Chill Milnot 2 hours before whipping.
Boil sugar and pineapple juice.
Let cool.
Mix with whipped Milnot.
Pour over angel food cake crumbs.
Add pineapple chunks and chill.

title: salsa
directions: In an enameled or stainless steel saucepan, combine tomatoes with vinegar.
Cover and cook until tomatoes are very soft, about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Puree briefly in batches in a blender or food processor.
Tomatoes should be slightly chunky. Return pureed tomatoes to the saucepan and add chili peppers, green peppers and onions.
Simmer until salsa thickens, about 1 hour. Add salt to taste.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until set.
Bake at 325°, uncovered.

title: chicken in the chipsfort collins, colorado
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 in greased 9 X 13 pan.
Top with 1 c. cheese and 1 cup chips.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg yolk until light.
Combine with milk.
Mix in another bowl the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Sift twice.
Stir into egg and milk mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in cooking oil.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Peel, quarter and slice thin the apples.
Stir into mixture.
Drop from spoon into hot fat.
Drain on soft paper. Serve hot with powdered sugar sprinkled on top.

title: short ribs with plums
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat in oil over medium heat. Remove meat. Keep warm. Add onion to the drippings. Saute onion until tender, scraping the pan to loosen browned bits. Drain. Add the salt, browning sauce, if desired, pepper, 3/4 cup water and dried plums. Bring to a boil. Return meat to the pan. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender. Remove meat. Keep warm. Skim fat from the pan. Combine the cornstarch and remaining water until smooth. Stir into pan drippings. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve with ribs and rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: betty's strawberry trifle
directions: In large mixer bowl, place instant pudding, sour cream and milk.
Beat at low speed until thick and mixed.
By hand, fold in whipped topping.
In large serving bowl, layer 1/2 of cake pieces, 1/3 strawberries and 1/2 pudding mix.
Repeat layers.
Arrange strawberries on top.

title: sweet and sour marinated vegetables
directions: Place cut up broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms and scallions in large bowl.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt, paprika, minced onions and garlic powder in a jar.
Shake until thoroughly mixed.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.

title: salmon log
directions: Combine first six items.
Shape into desired mold.
Chill overnight.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: french herb chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in tea ball or cheesecloth bag.
Add to French Herb Chicken as directed.
Remove before serving.

title: chinese beef chow
directions: Salt lightly, as soy sauce is salty.
Shred 1/2 head of lettuce and put in last.
Good served with crackers.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; beat until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Combine the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Good with caramel frosting.

title: noodle-rice casserole
directions: Saute raw noodles in butter in a saucepan until just golden. Add all other ingredients, except almonds.
Cover; simmer until rice is done, about 30 minutes, adding a little more broth if necessary to keep rice moist.
Turn into buttered casserole. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tea concentrate #1
directions: Cook water and sugar together about 3 minutes and pour over tea.
Cover and let stand until morning.
Remove the tea leaves and add the ReaLemon.
Freeze in quart containers.
Reconstitute 1 quart to 4 quarts water.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla, into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until blended.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool and add vanilla.
Use to make chocolate milk or anything you need chocolate syrup for.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white.
Add brown sugar.
Dip pecans in mixture. Place on baking sheet.
Bake about 30 minutes at 250°.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine salt, sugar and milk; add eggs, shortening and yeast.
Stir in flour (add more if needed).
Let stand until double in bulk.
Roll out; cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep, hot fat.
If desired, make a confectioners glaze and spread over tops while very hot.
"Holes" may be fried along with doughnuts.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: brownie pie
directions: Add cocoa, sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla to melted butter. Mix by spoon and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Pie will not look done.
Cool for a few minutes and top with ice cream and fudge sauce.

title: crab dip
directions: Marinate the crabmeat in the lemon juice. Blend together the whipped cream, cream cheese, grated cheese, pinch of salt, mayonnaise, onion, chives and garlic powder.
Fold in the crab (drained).
Add the Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and A.1. sauce. Let stand 2 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In casserole dish, put 1 pie crust in bottom.
Mix mushroom soup, Veg-All, cooked potatoes and onions and sour cream; stir well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Take other pie crust and put on top.
Take an egg, mix or stir well.
Use a brush to spread over crust, then it will not burn.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roasted bell pepper appetizer*
directions: Cut bell peppers in half and discard seeds.
Flatten halves with palm of your hand and place skin side up on a cookie sheet. Broil peppers until charred, then place in a Ziploc bag for 15 minutes.
Peel peppers and slice into 1/2-inch strips.
Place pepper strips in a bowl with remaining ingredients and mix.
Serve at room temperature or store in refrigerator.
Serve on individual plates on a bed of lettuce or as an hors d'oeuvre from the bowl with thin slices of French bread or crackers.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin, sugar and lemon juice for 5 minutes.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and chopped nuts and mix thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Blend rhubarb, lemon juice and sugar in saucepan.
Simmer until cooked and mushy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello for 2 minutes.
Pour into jars.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Set aside seasoning packet from noodle package.
Crush noodles.
Combine noodles and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes until crumbly.
Mix with salt and pepper.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: pork chops herbed
directions: Rub seasonings
into
chops.
Saute 7 minutes each side. Meanwhile, bring juice
and consomme to simmer.
Add pork chops and bake, covered for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over low flame. Add vanilla and food color. Add corn flakes making sure they're well coated. Spoon on wax paper. Garnish with red hots.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: southern tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: impossible cherry pie
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons margarine, sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup baking mix and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in mixer bowl.
Add milk, eggs and almond extract; beat for 1 minute or until smooth. Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Spoon pie filling on top. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup margarine, 1/2 cup baking mix, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in small bowl until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie.
Bake for 10 minutes or until topping is lightly browned.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sugar cookies to decorate(rich's cookies)
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add 1 egg and beat.
Add 1 egg yolk, lemon juice and vanilla; beat. Add flour and mix with a wooden spoon.
Divide dough in fourths. Wrap in plastic and chill several hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars together.
Add vanilla to beaten eggs and mix into sugar mixture.
Combine and sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add chips and nuts and stir well. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: indian pudding
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Heat 3 cups of milk and the molasses.
Mix corn meal, sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Gradually stir in hot milk mixture.
Add butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes or until thickened.
Pour into casserole.
Pour 1 cup of milk over pudding; do not stir.
Bake 3 hours.
If desired, serve with cream, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: pollo guisada(stove-top chicken)
directions: Rinse the chicken well.
Mix vinegar and mustard together. Pour over the chicken.
Rinse again in cool water.
Place in Dutch oven; set aside.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Topping: Cook blueberries and water a little, then add flour and sugar. Cook until thick; cool.

title: delicious punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May be colored to desired color by adding food coloring.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic until beef is crumbly; drain fat.
Mix in seasonings, tomato paste and hot water.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix
first 5 ingredients.
Place about 2 tablespoons of mixture
on wilted cabbage leaves and roll up.
Place in Dutch oven.
Pour
soup
over
the
rolls.
Cover and cook on top of stove on low heat until tender.
Add water, if needed.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Beat together ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: roman gnocchi
directions: Put 3 ounces of butter, some pepper, salt and grated nutmeg in the milk and bring to a boil.

Pour in the semolina, whisking all the time, and cook for 3 to 4 minutes. Remove the saucepan from the heat, and, still whisking energetically, incorporate 4 ounces of the Parmesan and the beaten egg.
Pour the mixture into a flat, buttered dish or tin in a layer about 1/2-inch deep. To make an even layer, dip the fingers in cold water and pat the semolina flat.
When it is cold, cut into rounds with a cutter or a glass 2 1/2-inches in diameter or into squares with a knife.

In either case, the utensil needs to be floured after each operation. Arrange the gnocchi, overlapping each other, in a buttered gratin dish. Sprinkle with the rest of the Parmesan and the rest of the butter (melted) and brown in the oven.

title: fruit spritzer punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (after thawing tangerine juice) together until thoroughly mixed. Add your choice of fruit to float on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine at low temperature.
Mix sugar and flour together and add to margarine.
Mix at low speed or stir until smooth.
