Add eggs.
Mix to keep smooth look.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth again.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and start out baking at 425° for 5 minutes.
Reduce to 400° and cook for 40 to 45 minutes until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Drain shrimp; pat dry.
Toss with mixture of dry ingredients until well coated.
Best if allowed to marinate overnight.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Mix jello and gelatine with boiling water; add strawberries and pineapple with juice to mixture and mix.
Put 2 1/2 cups of mixture in shallow 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over firm mixture and then add remaining mixture and cool.

title: molasses pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Mix in the molasses, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Stir in pecans dredged in flour.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until filling sets.

title: chocolate mounds
directions: Mix ingredients except peanut butter, oats and vanilla in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 1 or 2 minutes, just until smooth.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook onion in fat until tender.
Add rest of ingredients. Heat.

title: evil toffee squares
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with graham crackers.
Set aside.

title: country fried steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, but Crisco.
Put out on floured surface. Roll with pie like dough to about 1/2-inch thick.
Then cut in cube steak size, fry on top of stove until brown, using Crisco. Put in roaster pan.
Making gravy with drippings, pour over steak and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Do not have gravy too thick.
Serve hot.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Chill.
Serve as an appetizer or cold soup.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda, then add oil, eggs, vanilla, zucchini and walnuts.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Test.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Separate eggs. Add egg yolks one at a time, beat well. Add crushed vanilla wafers. In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Then combine egg whites with the mix. Add coconut and nuts. Pour into greased and floured Bunt or tube pan. Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 1/2 hours or until
toothpick comes out clean.

title: salmon mousse(serves 10)
directions: Dip bread in milk.
Drain milk well.
Mix with bread:
1 1/2 cans of salmon, eggs, cream and salt and pepper, using an electric mixer.
Add shrimp to mixture.
Pour half the mixture into a loaf pan.
Add remaining half can of salmon and olives, then top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let mousse cool in pan, then turn onto a serving platter and garnish with parsley and olives.
Can be made ahead.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Make thick sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add salmon. Season to taste.
Add cheese, cream and egg yolks.
Mix well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, then pour into souffle dish and bake in moderately hot oven (400°) for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and well risen.
Serve at once.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter; pour over stuffing mix.
Toss lightly.
In casserole dish, start by putting 1/3 of stuffing, a layer of chicken, onions, soup and broth.
Repeat this and end with remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage; set aside.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles. Place triangles with points toward center of 12-inch greased pizza pan (deep dish).
Press bottom and sides to form crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with hash browns and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Garnish with pimientos and fresh oregano, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir hamburger meat and onion in margarine in a 10-inch skillet until meat is light brown.
Stir in flour, garlic and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Stir in soup. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: garden pea casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery in margarine; add pimiento, water chestnuts and soup and mix well.
Fold in peas; top with cracker crumbs and bake in buttered dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen until ready to bake and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix butter, oil and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and add oil mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in bananas and nuts.
Bake in 2 well-greased pans at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the sugar and cream cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix together strawberries and strawberry liquid, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Fold fruit into cream cheese mixture.
Add whipped topping; fold until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or 2 smaller dishes.
Garnish with whole or sliced strawberries.
Freeze.
Defrost slightly before serving as a salad or dessert.

title: chicken salad deluxe
directions: Cook pasta; rinse and drain.
Combine all the remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add pasta.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Cream sugar and egg.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Add cherries and nuts.
Stir all together and bake in a greased and floured 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, Crisco, salt, vanilla and eggs and beat. Sift together flour and baking soda.
Blend together.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in baking dish.
Mix 1/3 cup dry bread crumbs and 1 cup grated cheese.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut the steak into strips.
Cut onions and peppers into strips. Put tomato sauce and tomatoes into pot or crock-pot.
Season to taste with spices.
Add steak, pepper and onions.
Cook until tender.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: strawberry jam bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Set aside. Combine sugar, butter and lemon juice in a large mixing bowl. Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir together jam and buttermilk.
Add to cream mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Mix well. Spoon batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until bread tests done.
Let cool before removing from pans.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli and onion in water until tender.
Add cheese and salt.
After cheese melts, add milk and stir.
Place in blender and process on medium until blended.
Heat to boiling.
If thicker soup is desired, mix 1/3 cup flour and 1/2 cup water.
Stir into soup.
Cook and stir until soup is the consistency of heavy cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce, stirring, until it becomes liquid. Soften Jell-O in cold water and dissolve in boiling cranberry juice.
Add liquid cranberry sauce and stir until blended.
Stir in Port wine.
Pour into 10 dessert or wine glasses and refrigerate until partially set.
Add water chestnuts and refrigerate until firm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onions, then milk, then just a little water, then egg.
Roll in balls 3/4-inch thick.
Cook in deep fryer until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
The batter may be stored in refrigerator overnight.

title: ma gillie's pokeweed and scrambled eggs
directions: Wash pokeweed leaves thoroughly; drain.
Put greens in saucepan.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes, or until tender.
Pour into colander and run cold water over to rinse it; drain.

title: grandma's cabbage(kapusta)
directions: Saute onion in shortening until tender.
Add paprika and mix well.
Add sliced cabbage, vinegar, water and salt.
Mix.
Cook under low heat until cabbage is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Cut broccoli flowerets from stem and place in a large bowl.
You can use broccoli stems if peeled.
Add raisins and chopped onions (green parts too).

title: summer salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix noodles, carrots, eggs, salt, pepper and Miracle Whip.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda.
Use juice and grated rind of orange.
Add enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add egg, nuts and chopped cranberries.
Stir well; pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: crunch punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 9 cups of boiling water.
Combine with 4 cups of sugar and 4 cups of water and bring to a boil; add Jell-O mixture.
Cool and add lemon and pineapple juice.
Pour into four 1/2 gallon milk cartons and freeze.
Set out to thaw until slushy. Put in punch bowl and add 1 quart ginger ale to each 1/2 gallon of mix.

title: party squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in 1/2 cup boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Place squash in large bowl and mash.
Stir in mayonnaise and next 8 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: marinade for steak or chops
directions: Add enough soy sauce to brown sugar to make a paste; coat steak or chops and let stand in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight.

title: apple pie slices
directions: Sift dry ingredients and then cut Crisco into flour mixture. Beat 1 egg yolk
and put in measuring cup and fill with milk until cup is 2/3 full.
Add to flour mixture and divide into two parts. Roll out one part and put on cookie sheet or into jellyroll pan. Prepare fresh apples as you would for pie.
(Peel, cut into slices, add sugar, flour and cinnamon.)
Place apple filling in pan, enough to fill to the top, and dot with butter.
Roll out the other part of the dough and place over the top.
Beat 1 egg white and spread this over the top crust to give a nice shiny appearance.
Bake at 375 degrees for 50 minutes.
When warm, glaze with 1 cup of powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons water.

title: citrus quencher
directions: In a large pitcher or container, combine the lemon juice, lime juice and sugar. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Stir in orange juice. Refrigerate until serving. Add soda and ice cubes. Garnish with lime if desired. Yield: 3 quarts.

title: sauteed sirloin and mushrooms
directions: Cut steak into four serving-size pieces. Sprinkle with garlic pepper. In a 10 inch skillet, cook steaks in hot butter or margarine over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until desired doneness, turning once. Remove steaks from pan; cover and keep warm. For mushroom glaze, carefully add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce to skillet. Cook and stir until bubbly, scraping brown bits from bottom of the pan. Stir in onions and mushrooms. Cook over medium-high heat about 8 minutes or until tender and the glaze is reduced by half it's volume (to 1 cup). Transfer warm steak to dinner plates and spoon glaze atop.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chips or crumbs.
Put in buttered casserole and top with chips or crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Do not dilute soups or evaporated milk.

title: sweet corn casserole
directions: Place oleo in a large skillet; heat slowly. Peel and slice sweet potatoes. Peel, core and slice apples. Add sugar. Cook/fry slowly, turning often.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter, then add egg yolks; blend well, then add crushed bananas.
Add your dry ingredients and alternate with the milk.
Lastly beat your egg whites stiff and fold into the batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Mix ingredients by hand; mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (buttered).

title: sauerkraut
directions: Note:
Do this over and over until you get stone jar full.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, then debone the chicken.
Reserve the water that the chicken was cooked in, this is to be used to cook the spaghetti.
Lightly brown celery, green peppers, onion in 2 Tbsp. of bacon drippings or margarine.
Combine spaghetti with all other ingredients.
Add to taste any or all of the following seasonings: Black pepper, salt, garlic powder, oregano, ground cumin.
Place in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes (first 20 minutes covered with aluminum foil).

title: grandmother seal's sour cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks, sour cream and raisins. Cook until thick.

title: molasses cake
directions: Heat oven
to
In
a
large
bowl combine flour, sugar and
cinnamon.
Add melted butter, beaten eggs, molasses and vanilla.
Beat
3 minutes with electric mixer.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Put drained pineapple in pan, boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Break small pieces of cream cheese and add to hot mixture and beat until smooth.
Remove and add cherries, nuts and marshmallows.
Beat whipping cream until it forms stiff peaks. Fold into jello mixture.
Chill until firm.
Overnight is best. Keep refrigerated.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: To make cheese sauce, melt 2 Tbsp. butter, blend in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk; cook until thick.
Add salt, pepper and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Set aside. Saute ham and green onion in 3 Tbsp. butter until onion is tender. Add eggs and cook over medium heat until eggs are set; stir in the mushrooms and cheese sauce.
Spoon eggs into a greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Combine melted butter and bread crumbs; spread evenly over egg mixture.
Cover; chill overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo peanut soup
directions: Combine flour and paprika, then coat chicken pieces.
In large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown chicken slowly in hot cooking oil over medium heat about 15 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Cook green pepper and onion in pan drippings until tender but not brown.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add water, tomatoes, salt, cayenne and chicken pieces to pan.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
In small saucepan, heat peanut butter on low until melted; gradually blend in about 1 cup hot chicken broth from mixture.
Return all to chicken mixture.
Stir in okra and shrimp; return to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
May serve over bed of hot rice.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Place remaining ingredients into bowl.
Add hamburg mixture.
Toss together with taco or Thousand Island dressing. Serve with whole tortilla chips and tomato wedges.

title: pink frozen salad
directions: (For more tart flavor, I add a small amount of ReaLemon juice.)

title: corn meal fried shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip shrimp in batter; fry until golden brown.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg; beat. Drain cherries (save juice).
Slice and set aside.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and cherry juice.
Mix well.
Fold in vanilla, pecans and cherries.
Use 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Grate rind of one lemon into mixture.
Bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
After it is baked and while still hot, frost with glaze.

title: honey spiced acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half, scoop out seeds and discard. Place squash, cut side down, on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn squash over.
Combine spices, add honey and margarine, stirring well.
Brush squash with honey mixture; spoon remaining mixture into center of each squash.
Bake 5 to 40 minutes longer or until squash is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: quick frankfurter stew
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Stir in soup, water, frankfurters and hot pepper sauce. Cook 5 minutes or until heated thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: "hershey bar pie"
directions: Melt Hershey bars and then mix (fold) with Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust and put in refrigerator for a couple of hours until firm.
Cut, serve and enjoy!

title: jambalaya(microwave fish and seafood)
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, combine oil, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cover with lid; microwave on High for 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in chicken, sausage, rice, V-8 juice, hot sauce, thyme and bay leaf.
Cover; microwave on High for 10 minutes or until bubbling, stirring once during cooking.
Stir again.
Reduce power to 50%.
Cover; microwave 10 minutes or until rice is nearly done.
Stir in shrimp and parsley.
Cover; microwave at 50% power for 5 minutes or until most shrimp is opaque, stirring once during cooking.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes or until shrimp are opaque. Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: different pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs
into
milk
and
stir
well.
Add vanilla and salt. Stir good, then add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: limping susan
directions: Cut okra, onion and bacon in small pieces, then saute together in pan until bacon is cooked.
Add rice, salt and water.
Cover and cook on medium heat until all liquid is gone, about 20 minutes.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix well. Fold in small Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Sprinkle toasted, chopped pecans on top, if desired.

title: quick skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in water, tomatoes, Heinz 57 sauce, salt and sugar.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: my mother-in-law's coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl. Add butter, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 coconut.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: alba's sees fudge
directions: Cook sugar, salt and milk to medium ball stage.
Put marshmallow cream, butter (cut up), chocolate chips and vanilla in large bowl.
Pour over the hot sugar-milk mix.
Beat until firm; add nuts.
Pour in greased pan.
The best.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown chops in skillet; remove fat.
Sprinkle chops with pepper.
Place slice of onion and pepper ring on each chop.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: upside-down chocolate cake
directions: Place marshmallows in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine sugar, cocoa and water; pour over marshmallows.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon cake batter over marshmallow mixture.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 15 servings.

title: doris' homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all of the above together in large bowl.
Pour into freezer can.
Finish filling with whole milk.
Freeze until freezer handle is difficult to turn.
Remove paddle and replace lid.
Pack in salt and ice until ready to serve.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt shortening in an oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Put flour in a plastic bag and place 1 piece of chicken at a time and shake it.
Place all chicken in pan and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Return to oven.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: country fried pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt in frying pan.
Brown pork chops using no fat. Pour ingredients over top.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Measure sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until peanut butter melts and mixture is well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins, peanuts and Kellogg's cereal, mixing well until coated.
Press into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Makes sixteen 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: grammy's chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rice in bottom of the pan, uncooked.
Pour onion soup over rice.
Place chicken cutlets in pan. Pour mushroom soup over cutlets.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 15 minutes.
Serve with chicken gravy.

title: special lemony chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; shake to coat.
In large skillet, brown chicken in margarine.
Add juice and mushrooms.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until chicken and mushrooms are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: popcorn salad
directions: In bowl, combine popcorn, sliced onion, diced celery, mayonnaise, bacon, cheese and water chestnuts.
Chill.
Top with reserved bacon and grated cheese.
Best when served within 3 to 4 hours.

title: vegetable log
directions: Coarsely grate onion, celery and carrots.
Crumble crackers well and add.
Mix well.
Knead in butter.
Separate into 2 parts, put on greased foil and roll like a log.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: devilishly delicious angel cake
directions: Place frozen Heath bars into a heavy duty plastic bag and break into small pieces with meat mallet.
Mix crushed candy bars into container of Cool Whip and stir until candy is evenly distributed throughout whipped topping.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash the bananas.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, flour, salt, soda and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan (greased and floured) for 45 minutes in a moderate oven at 325° to 350°.

title: salami sail boats
directions: Cut pickles into halves lengthwise and make a lengthwise slit in each pickle on the cut side. Cut salami into shapes of sails and insert into the slit. Flute the edges of sail with cream cheese pressed through a pastry tube. Makes 6 hors d'oeuvres. Sparkling as the conversation around them.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Bring fruit, butter, sugar
and
syrup to a boil, stirring constantly.
Set aside and partially cool.
Grease a tube pan. Cut biscuits into
pieces
each
and roll into balls. Place in tube pan in
layers;
put syrup over each layer until all is used. Bake in
400° oven about 25 minutes.
Serve hot; pull apart with fork to serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients gently but thoroughly by hand.
Bake in 8-inch round dish at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: swedish apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a pan.
Add water.
Sift flour and cinnamon. Cut butter and sugar with a fork.
Spread all over the apples. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: simone's cheesy squash
directions: Wash and slice squash, then boil until tender, then drain.
In a skillet, heat oil and add diced onion and saute.
Add drained squash and dry ingredients; cook until brown, then stir in cheese until melted.

title: peanut whirls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then add milk and blend.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick into rectangle.
Melt chocolate bits over hot water.
Spread on rolled dough.
Roll jelly roll fashion and chill 1/2 hour.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Pour oil in deep mixing bowl.
Add milk, then meal.
Stir, then add corn, pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Last, add cheese and mix.
Bake at 425° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples.
Coat with lemon juice to prevent discoloring. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Crumble butter, flour and brown sugar with fingers over apples.
Bake in a buttered pie plate
at 450° for 10 minutes and then at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: venison stew
directions: Cut the venison into 1-inch cubes.
Roll in flour and brown in a small amount of oil.
Add the boiling water and black pepper to the browned meat.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add the diced vegetables and simmer until tender. Use 2 tablespoons of flour moistened with water to thicken the remaining liquid.

title: peaches 'n cream
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Drain the peaches and save the juice.
Combine 3/4 cup self-rising flour with the package of pudding, margarine, egg and milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread in pan.
Put peaches on top of batter, leaving about 1/2-inch from the sides uncovered.
Beat for 2 minutes the cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons peach juice.
Spoon this over the peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lightly spoon flour into cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all bar and frosting ingredients, except chocolate chips, at low speed until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom of prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown. Sprinkle immediately with chocolate chips; let stand 5 minutes, then spread evenly.

title: blackened cajun green beans
directions: Blanch beans in boiling water.
Drain and cool slightly. Pour oil over beans and toss to cover well.
Place beans in a Ziploc bag with seasoning and cornmeal.
Shake well to coat beans.
Melt butter in an iron skillet and saute beans until slightly blackened.
Serves 4 - 5.

title: oven pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Put in a casserole dish, add the uncooked rice, soup and the bouillon cube, which has been dissolved in 1 cup hot water.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until tender with lid on.

title: west coast freezer
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, nuts and oleo together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and oleo.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, coconut and pecans and mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
When done, spread jar of marshmallow cream on hot cake.
Cool and then frost.

title: good chicken
directions: Put chicken in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: depression bread
directions: Completely dissolve yeast in warm water; mix in remaining ingredients.
Allow to rise to twice its size. Then punch down dough, pinch into roll size pieces and place in greased pan. Allow rolls to rise to twice their size.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and brush tops with butter.
May need to be baked longer.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well, then put in freezer for 1 to 2 hours.
Take out of freezer and roll into balls. Put back into freezer.
Take 1 1/2 or 2 bags chocolate chips and 1 square paraffin and melt over medium-low heat.
When all is melted, start taking out the peanut butter balls that are in the freezer and take a toothpick or crochet hook and put balls on, one at a time and dip in chocolate.
Leave chocolate turned on even when dipping.
After you get all the balls covered in chocolate, take a teaspoon and pour a little chocolate over the holes which the toothpicks made.
Keep in freezer so they don't melt.

title: minestrone(soup)
directions: Heat oil and butter in a 5-quart Dutch oven pan over medium heat.
Add onions; saute, stirring until soft and golden, 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in carrots, celery, green beans and potato; saute 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, cabbage and garlic; saute for 3 minutes. Add broth, water and liquid from tomatoes.
Add tomatoes, salt, basil, rosemary, pepper and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans to soup.
Cook, uncovered, until soup is thick, 30 to 40 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 12 cups, 8 to 10 servings.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: iowa corn casserole
directions: In a skillet, fry the bacon until lightly browned.
Remove and set aside.
Pour 1/8 to 1/4 cup of bacon drippings over breadcrumbs.
Set aside.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons of remaining drippings.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender. Stir in corn and bacon.
Spoon into a 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp-vegetable dish
directions: Combine shrimp, vegetables, sugar and spices to hot vegetable oil.
Saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain any oil left in pan.
Dissolve cornstarch and wine together.
Add to vegetables.
Bring to boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with rice, if desired.
Excellent for light lunch.
Serves 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar together. Place in bottom of pan evenly; bake at 400° for 18 minutes. Cool.
Mix 1 cup sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese together until smooth; spread on top of pretzels evenly.
Mix jello and water; add strawberries.
When jello starts to jell, spread on top of cream cheese.
Put in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Mix the sugar with the 7 cups hot water and add to the tea bags and 2 cups boiling water.
Add the remaining ingredients. Freeze overnight.
Spoon in glasses and add 7-Up.

title: mounds cake
directions: Sift the flour with the baking powder and salt. Set aside. Cream the butter and sugar very hard until silvery and light.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: pumpkin pie cake(this is yummy and serves 12 good sized pieces)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Mix them well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: canned apple relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Add salt and water.
Let stand 15 minutes and drain.
Remove cores and chop apples with skins on. Add apples, vinegar and sugar to pepper and onion mixture.
Add cloth bag containing spices and cook 10 or 15 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls using a level tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Crush 2 1/2 cups cornflakes.
Roll each ball of dough in cornflakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with maraschino cherry.
Bake in moderate oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: southern barbecued chicken
directions: Mix soup, honey, mustard and onion powder.
Place chicken on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 30 minutes or until no longer pink, turning and brushing often with soup mixture.
Serves 4.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cream in a small saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Let boil about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add enough powdered sugar to make of spreading consistency. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove bone and cut into bite size pieces. Crumble 3/4 stack of crackers.
Melt margarine in 6 x 12-inch baking dish; add crackers to make crust.
Place chicken pieces on crust.
Mix soups, sour cream, water chestnuts and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble remaining crackers on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: best vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except green onions if desired. Fresh vegetables.
Yield: about 2 cups.

title: baked short ribs mount vernon
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Roll short ribs in mixture. Brown ribs on all sides in butter in skillet.
Reduce heat. Add onions and cook until tender, but not brown. Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard, catsup, beer and bouillon.
Turn ribs and other ingredients into 2-quart casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for
1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots. Bake 1 hour longer.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, milk, butter and vanilla together in baking dish.
Add corn.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: sweet yogurt topping
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl; mix well and chill.
Makes a great topping for fruit.
Each serving provides 1/4 milk; 16 optional calories.
Serves 4.

title: quick stuffing
directions: In a large bowl, combine all
ingredients,
except
the butter.
Mix well.	Coat a pan with the
melted
butter.
Pour the dressing into the pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand until ready to serve. Serve over Rodney's Biscuits.
Serves 6.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use 9 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until thawed.
Mix all other ingredients. Add broccoli. Spread with cracker crumbs. Bake in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cocktail meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix well. Roll into 1/2-ounce size balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Mix together jelly and chili sauce.
Heat until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs.
Stir and coat, simmer for few minutes. Can also use small cocktail wieners or Vienna sausages.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Add bread to milk; mix in next 5 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Brown meatballs in oil in large skillet. Prepare gravy mix according to directions using 1 1/4 cups water. Blend in mayonnaise.
Add meatballs and heat.
Makes about 45 meatballs.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4 quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or 250° for 4 1/2 hours until tender.

title: mother's homemade ice cream(vanilla; 6 quarts equals 1 gallon)
directions: You will need a strainer, large boiler, ice cream churn and ice cream salt.

title: cuban black beans and rice
directions: Heat ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 can cooked black beans.
Add 4 cups cooked brown rice.

title: braised chicken and cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove chicken from bones.
Add chicken to drippings from bacon and turn once 6 to 8 minutes until colored and brown.
Remove chicken.
Add water and stir to scrape up brown bits on bottom of pans.
Stir in soup mix, cabbage, carrots, thyme and bacon.
Return chicken to pot.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat 35 to 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally until vegetables are tender and chicken is light.
Stir in black-eyed peas until cooked through (taste peas for tenderness).
Makes 4 servings, 381 calories, 38 g protein, 13 g fat.

title: puree of onion and potato soup
directions: Dice onions to about 1/3-inch size.
Put 1 tablespoon butter in a large kettle.
Add onions and cook, covered, over low heat, until tender, but not brown.
Stir occasionally.

title: grandma small's salad dressing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add Miracle Whip, hot water and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and toss gently.
Combine oil, orange juice, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss gently.
Chill 1 hour.
Drain off liquids.
Stir mayonnaise into salad.
Yields 6 servings.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown onions and ground beef.
Drain.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, seasoned salt and sugar.
Cook at low heat.
Cook noodles according to the package directions.
Using a fork, mash cream cheese and sour cream together.
Grease a medium-size casserole dish.
Layer first with noodles, then meat mixture, then cream cheese mixture.
Top casserole with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches, apricots, pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges. Mix together with pudding.
Add strawberries.
Let set overnight. Just before serving, add bananas.

title: beets with orange sauce
directions: Mix salt, cornstarch and orange juice in a saucepan.
Cook mixture, stirring constantly, until it has thickened.
Add beets to the sauce and stir carefully.
Heat mixture through and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine yeast and 2 tablespoons warm water in a bowl. Let stand 5 minutes. Combine yeast mixture, oil and remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Stir until smooth. Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 4 hours or up to 4 days.

title: one minute fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook.
Watch for mixture to come to rolling boil.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
"Do not stir when boiling."
Remove from heat.
Beat with mixer until thick; add nuts.
Drop onto wax paper by spoon.
Cool.

title: mom zuccaro's chicken
directions: You will need a plastic bag (for shaking ingredients).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add onion and bell pepper. Mix in a bowl Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup and milk or water. Layer in casserole dish the tortillas, beef mixture and soup mixture. Add grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: zesty ketchup spread
directions: Stir ingredients together in a small mixing bowl.

title: flat dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt in medium mixing bowl.
Add margarine. Work together with fingers until they are mixed as well as you can get them.
Add beaten egg and milk; make a dough which you turn out on a board.
Then you start working more flour into it; keep working more flour into it until it won't hold anymore.
Roll it as thin as though you were going to
make noodles.
Cut them in strips.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Cook sugar and water until it spins a thin thread, then cool. Beat egg whites until stiff, add syrup (sugar and water) and chocolate.
Fold in whipped cream, vanilla and nuts.

title: nikki's cheesecake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix first 5 ingredients well. Roll out 1 package of crescent rolls in pan.
Spread seams together.
Spread cheese mixture over "crust."
Roll 2nd package crescent rolls over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top while hot. Slice when cool.

title: melt-in-your-mouth quick chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Blend soup with broth and tarragon.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange egg slices over chicken.
Combine flour, buttermilk and butter; mix well.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until crust rises to top and is golden brown. Serves 6.

title: eight minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.
Serves 10 people. Enjoy!

title: one dish meal
directions: With a little water, boil the potatoes for about 8 minutes. Meanwhile, brown the hamburger in a skillet with the onion.
Drain potatoes and put in casserole dish or loaf pan.
Add hamburger and onion. Mix. Pour the tomato puree over it and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fish steak
directions: Marinate fish in sauce for 2 to 3 hours.
Coat both sides of fish.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn and broil 5 more minutes.
Or, bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Or, grill on foil over open flame.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves, then add to egg mixture.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out then prick surface with toothpick.
Drizzel Glaze over cake.

title: deluxe chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute chicken and onion in butter 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, carrots, celery, broth, wine, parsley, chives, dry mustard, garlic, chervil, peppers, Worcestershire and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine cornstarch with water and stir into chicken mixture.
Cook to boiling and remove from heat.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream and cheeses.
Roll out 1/2 pastry for bottom crust and fit it in a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Spoon in chicken.
Roll out and cut remaining pastry into strips to form a lattice top.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coffee orange fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.

In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, water, eggs, pudding mix, coffee liqueur, orange peel and cinnamon.	Beat with electric mixer on low until blended.	Beat on medium speed four more minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan.	Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and sift powdered sugar on top.

title: persimmon and date bar cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in greased and floured 10 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
